Name: Business Intelligence Analyst II
Description: Accelerate Your CareerDrive global technology    With more than $2 billion in revenues, CDK Global is a leading global provider of integrated information technology and digital marketing solutions to the automotive retail and adjacent industries. Focused on enabling end-to-end automotive commerce, CDK provides solutions to dealers in more than 100 countries around the world, serving approximately 28,000 retail locations and most automotive manufacturers. CDK Global solutions automate and integrate critical processes from pre-sale targeted advertising to the sale, financing, insurance, parts supply, repair and maintenance of vehicles, with an increasing focus on utilizing data analytics and predictive intelligence.     We’re large enough to make a difference but small enough for your voice to be heard. This means that we are an organization where every person matters. You can make an impact on the success of our business and that of our customers regardless of what career you decide to pursue.     From data scientists to sales and client service experts, we’re hiring to support your growth and ours - Green light your career.    PRINCIPLE DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES    CDK Digital Marketing is seeking a BI Data Analyst II who will help guide stakeholders media optimization & financial forecasting, while having the technical skills to build and implement those solutions through our Enterprise Data Warehouse and Tableau visualization tools. This role will report directly to the Director of Media & Partnerships through the Product Management Organization.     The successful candidate will be able to think strategically about business issues and will have a strong command of data warehousing platforms, reporting automation, data visualization, digital marketing analytics and basic statistics.     The BI Data Analyst II should be able to think strategically about business issues and understand CDK’s Product & Service portfolios and how they relate to our Clients. Candidates with a history of owning data driven projects and overcoming obstacles are desired. The BI Data Analyst II will be able to take direction, but will also pro-actively drive projects to completion.     The BI Data Analyst II is curious about data. The ideal candidate is not intimidated by large and complex data sets and is naturally inclined to view things from an analytical perspective. Digital Advertising experience is desired.     The successful candidate will work closely with advertising product managers, agency senior leadership, BI engineers, and other data analysts. Because of this, they must be able to present the results of complex data analytics to a non-technical audience in a clear and concise manner.     The BI Data Analyst II must be able to extract data from CDK’s data warehouses, data lake, ad platform, pixel logs, and other data sources. A comfortable relationship with various flavors of SQL and experience with a fact/dimension based Data Warehouse is essential.  Extracted data will be manipulated, merged, and analyzed to produce reports, graphs, dashboards and other output to ultimately reveal performance of our products for internal and external users.     The successful candidate will have a history of simplifying and/or automating labor intensive, data based projects. The BI Data Analyst II will strive to reduce the number of day-to-day reporting tasks, allowing them to focus on strategic projects and deliver insights to stakeholders.     CDK embraces Agile Development methodology. As a member of the Analyst team, the Candidate will help define requirements, identify roadblocks and track the progress of all open projects.      At CDK Digital Marketing, we are the leading provider of digital marketing solutions to the automotive industry. CDK’s customers are all part of the Automotive ecosystem, ranging from Manufacturers, Agencies, Dealer Groups and Dealers. The CDK Data Warehouse, which is at the center of CDK’s analytics products & solutions, is the largest "in-market" automotive data warehouse in the world. Desired candidates will have experience analyzing websites, advertising or digital media performance.          KNOWLEDGE, SKILLS AND ABILITIES    Education: BA/BS in a business or technical field; an Advanced Degree is a plus  Experience Level: 3-6 Years    Experience with Data Warehousing platforms (Oracle, SQL Server, Etc...)Experience with multiple reporting & visualization techniques.Experience with website and digital media analytics.Strong MS Excel and Database skills.Strong SQL skills.Experience with digital marketing concepts, cookies (1st & 3rd party), pixel tags, privacy standards, SEO, social media, advertising attribution methods & models.Proven ability to multi-task, handle multiple priorities and adapt to a fast-paced environment.Experience defining products & solutions containing large data sets from multiple sources.3+ years’ experience in a Data Analyst role.3+ years’ experience writing SQL queries against a data warehouse or similar data store.3+ years’ experience with data visualization using tools such as R, Tableau, ExcelDemonstrated ability to communicate technical topics to non-technical audiencesComfortable presenting results to stakeholders and writing technical summariesBackground in web analytics, online advertising, or ad agency experience a plusAutomotive vertical experience a plusPrior software engineering experience a plus      ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS   Communicate with business consultants, agency partners and enterprise sales to gather and understand requirements.Visualization of data using tools such as Tableau, Excel, R, etc...Ability to manage a backlog, establish priorities, multi-task and work proactively and independently.Data mining from data warehouse, using SQL, RegEx, json, pixel logs, and other big data formats.Analyze web analytics and other quantitative and qualitative data.Data discovery and data cleansing.Communicate complex technical issues to non-technical team members.Improve the efficiency of the team by automating data projects.    CDK Global knows you have passions outside of work. You have family, friends, sporting events, and lots of things going on. That’s why we offer a comprehensive benefits package to not only take care of you but your family as well. All of our benefits are effective the first day of employment including 401K matching, paid time off to re-energize, donate your time to volunteer in your community, and tuition reimbursement to name a few.  At CDK, we pride ourselves on having a diverse workforce. We value and celebrate the uniqueness of individuals and the different perspectives they provide. We offer equal opportunity employment regardless of race, color, religion, gender, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, genetics, disability status, age, marital status, or protected veteran status.

Name: BUSINESS SYSTEMS ANALYST
Description: BUSINESS SYSTEMS ANALYST Req #: 162612 Department: UW INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY Appointing Department Web Address: http://www.washington.edu/uwit/employment/ Job Location: Seattle Campus Posting Date: 11/29/2018 Closing Info: Open Until Filled Salary: Commensurate with experience Shift: First Shift Notes:If you would like to find out more about what it is like to work for UW-IT, as well as to get a feel for our culture and our people, visit us at our employment website. As a UW employee, you have a unique opportunity to change lives on our campuses, in our state and around the world. UW employees offer their boundless energy, creative problem solving skills and dedication to build stronger minds and a healthier world.  UW faculty and staff also enjoy outstanding benefits, professional growth opportunities and unique resources in an environment noted for diversity, intellectual excitement, artistic pursuits and natural beauty. All of which has allowed the UW to be nationally recognized as a “Great College to Work For” for five consecutive years. UW Information Technology (UW-IT) is the central information technology organization for the University of Washington, responsible for strategic planning, oversight, and direction of the UW’s IT infrastructure, resources, and services. UW-IT provides critical technology support to all three campuses, UW medical centers, and research operations around the world. UW-IT partners with the University community to enable innovation, learning, discovery, and service.  Academic Services (AS) is the division of UW-IT that develops and supports enterprise academic and student administrative systems. The Student Information System (SIS) Program, in turn, has responsibility for systems that directly support the entire student lifecycle - including admissions, academic planning, registration, financial aid, and student accounts - as well as those that enable it, such as curriculum management. The SIS Program engages the UW community in visioning a technology enabled future that supports the broader goals of the university. We are currently seeking a Business Analyst with project management experience to support our efforts to modernize these systems. The incumbent will conduct and direct analysis efforts, planning, designing and testing on one or two work streams within a diverse team environment that includes representatives from a broad range of campus and administrative units.  Due to the level of ambiguity and complexity of requirements, the incumbent must have strong intellectual curiosity and the ability to constructively question and influence thought partners across functional areas and end-user audiences.  Due to the number of diverse stakeholders and the matrixed organization structure, the incumbent must be able to communicate complex processes, problems, and solutions in a simple, compelling, accurate, and highly visual manner for all levels of the organization.  The quality of work completed by this position will have a direct impact on the experience of prospective and enrolled students, as well as administrative processes at the UW.  Through this and other related modernization efforts, the UW will develop a highly effective student information system. The new system will bring 21st century capabilities to UW students, faculty and staff and dramatically improve student and faculty services and increase staff efficiency. The Business Analyst will directly impact the quality and value of the products delivered through these efforts. Requirements: Bachelors degree in Computer Science, Business Administration, or similar degree Four years of experience doing progressively more complex business analysis within a project or program environment such as scope definition, requirements gathering, business process re-engineering, etc. In depth understanding and working knowledge of various software development and service management methodologies/concepts (e.g. Agile, Kanban, ITIL, Waterfall). Demonstrated experience with a variety of research and analysis techniques, ideally including a mix of both quantitative and qualitative methods for understanding and documenting end-user and business owner requirements. Demonstrated ability to perform data analysis, including querying standard databases using SQL. Self-starter and able to manage multiple priorities and tasks in a dynamic environment. Demonstrated excellent written/oral communication skills, technical documentation skills, user liaison skills, and personal interaction abilities. Demonstrated ability to work independently and as part of a team in a cooperative effort. Ability to deal with trade-offs, conflict, and change management in a collaborative and positive manner. Desired: Familiarity with Higher Education in general and the student administration domain in particular Relevant coursework in business analysis, business requirement documentation, standards-based modeling technologies, or quality assurance Conditions: Ongoing employment will be dependent on performance, as well as availability of funds.  This position contributes in a collaborative team work environment. Collaboration is supported through a shared space working environment, ad hoc meetings focused on problem-solving, and the use of a variety of communication tools. Responsibility to work varied hours as needed to meet project deadlines and to accomplish work assignments on which others’ activities depend. Expectation to go over and above as necessary to achieve agreed upon goals and outcomes within the student program. Daily interactions with other team members, subject matter experts and stakeholders at all levels of the organization. Application Process: The application process for UW positions may include completion of a variety of online assessments to obtain additional information that will be used in the evaluation process. These assessments may include Work Authorization, Cover Letter and/or others. Any assessments that you need to complete will appear on your screen as soon as you select “Apply to this position”. Once you begin an assessment, it must be completed at that time; if you do not complete the assessment you will be prompted to do so the next time you access your “My Jobs” page. If you select to take it later, it will appear on your "My Jobs" page to take when you are ready. Please note that your application will not be reviewed, and you will not be considered for this position until all required assessments have been completed.REQUIREMENTS: See aboveThe University of Washington is a leader in environmental stewardship & sustainability, and committed to becoming climate neutral.The University of Washington is an equal opportunity, affirmative action employer. Description: SENIOR BI BUSINESS ANALYST Req #: 159137 Department: SCHOOL OF MEDICINE Job Location: Health Sciences Center Posting Date: 08/17/2018 Closing Info: Open Until Filled Salary: Salary is commensurate with experience and education. Shift: First Shift Notes: As a UW employee, you will enjoy generous benefits and work/life programs.  For detailed information on Benefits for this position, click here. As a UW employee, you have a unique opportunity to change lives on our campuses, in our state and around the world. UW employees offer their boundless energy, creative problem solving skills and dedication to build stronger minds and a healthier world.  UW faculty and staff also enjoy outstanding benefits, professional growth opportunities and unique resources in an environment noted for diversity, intellectual excitement, artistic pursuits and natural beauty. All of which has allowed the UW to be nationally recognized as a “Great College to Work For” for five consecutive years. The School of Medicine (SOM) has an outstanding opportunity for a Senior BI Business Analyst. The Operations and Financial Reporting Department, Office of the Dean, provides financial oversight and analysis of the Dean's Office departments as well as academic departments’ financial activities within the SOM. Under the general direction of the Director for Departmental Computing, the Senior BI Business Analyst serves as a flexible resource that works independently to examine and analyze administrative systems, fiscal and/or administrative records, and institutional practices. The Senior BI Business Analyst reports to management on results, provides impact assessments, and recommends training and improvement in operations and information systems. This position has a wide range of responsibilities to include requirement gathering for projects, acting as the point of contact for SOM clients, financial reporting and analysis, operational assessments, and documenting projects, systems, and processes. This position acts in an advisory capacity to senior management in the School providing research and analytical support on data and reporting issues. Must demonstrate effective project management analysis and sound business judgment.  Interpreting, analyzing and disseminating rules, policies and procedures, as well as ensuring staffs’ accurate understanding and application, is critical. This position must provide technical expertise in the integration of financial information from several sources (UW Financial Accounting System (FAS), School of Medicine department shadow systems, University of Washington Medical Center, Harborview Medical Center, as well as affiliates such as Seattle Children’s Hospital and the Fred Hutchinson Cancer Research Center). This position must determine which data is necessary, the source of the data and the most efficient method for obtaining the data and converting to a format consistent with the Academic Medical Center reporting requirements. It will be necessary to make theoretical or subjective judgments with respect to compatibility of data between different organizations (i.e. mapping of financial statement interfaces between organizations). New approaches, methods or techniques will be required to align School of Medicine departments and outside organizations’ processes to provide information necessary for consolidated financial statements. Business Analysis Apply user centered design practices, interview stakeholders and system users to determine functional requirements for new and existing systems. Facilitate discussions with stakeholders and subject matter experts to research and analyze the end-users needs. Create documentation to support understanding of business needs and document the project requirements.  Identify, develop and evaluate solutions encompassing a variety of automated and manual techniques, considering programming complexity, on-going technical support requirements and department end user workflow where applicable.  Review new or modified program, including documentation, diagram, and flowchart, to determine if program will perform according to user request and conform to guidelines. Create project documentation as necessary in support of agile development techniques.  Analyze information systems, data base models and/or interface needs. Evaluate information gathered from multiple sources and ensure accuracy and completion of the data. Partner with developers to test and validate the data.  Write, revise, and verify quality standards and test procedures for program design and product evaluation to attain quality of software. Work with the users to test the requested changes and document the results. Provide trainings and presentations on new products/features, as needed.  Provide support with analytical, design, and development tasks associated with the implementation of information system solutions.  Provide on-going support to clients by correlating user needs with information system design and communicate with the department’s developers  Help prioritize, troubleshoot, and resolve system and service problems, in order to provide very reliable and highly available computing services.  Collect and assemble data needed for various SOM surveys. Project Management Serve in a project management capacity over low to moderately complex projects. Work with formal and informal project plans, and work independently or in a group to meet deadlines.  Identify appropriate level of oversight and resource requirements, facilitate team member activities and communicate project progress with management, developers, customers, and users.  Use solid judgment to determine appropriate escalation and resolution of issues within project structure. Work with management to evaluate and communicate business issues and impact.  Help managing competing stakeholder priorities and assist in identifying best approach to meet expected deadlines. Other Related Duties as Assigned Complete special projects for the dean and executive leadership.  Develop cross-training for staff on reporting, databases, and external resources. DESIREDProficient in SQL and VB Scripting, MS Access, Crystal and MS SQL Reporting Services.Knowledge of University of Washington financial systems.Experience with academic medical center financial reporting.Recent experience with financial reporting applications (such as general ledger) conversion or installation. Name: Senior Analyst, Venture
Description: In just a little over a decade, PitchBook has grown into a global organization with offices in Seattle, San Francisco, New York and London. With consistent high double-digit growth since 2009, the company has become the industry’s leading source of private market data, serving more than 3,000 clients around the world.  As a four-time winner of the Best Workplaces in Washington award, PitchBook is committed to fostering an open, collaborative work environment driven by excellence, inclusion and fun. Our culture is at the heart of our success, and it’s something we work on every day.  Our primary home for the last decade, PitchBook’s Seattle office has grown from humble beginnings in a 200-square-foot windowless room to our current three-floor home in a downtown skyscraper. Located just blocks away from Pike Place Market and historic Pioneer Square, our headquarters boast stunning mountain views, open collaboration spaces and a startup culture that emphasizes hard work and camaraderie. Working in our Seattle office means growing your career alongside smart, dedicated people in the city where it all began.  Job Overview Our Research Analyst group is looking to hire a Senior Analyst to join our venture team. As a valued team member you’ll hone your existing analytical skills, develop meaningful insight into a fascinating industry, and contribute to our venture capital research. The notes and reports this team produces are utilized by many of the largest private capital investors, investment banks and service providers globally. Our team is creative, driven and focused on providing the most actionable research to our readers and clients. ResponsibilitiesConduct research and analysis across the venture capital industry, as well as trends in venture debt markets, the innovation economy and other relevant spacesEstablish research frameworks to provide independent commentary, evaluations and forecasts around our primary coverage areas, while identifying unique themes that may impact venture marketsUtilize proprietary PitchBook data, the internet, newspapers, academic white papers, public and private company research notes, trade journals, trade shows and economic indicator forecasts, etc. to inform and develop actionable analysisManage research pipeline and analyst workflowWrite and edit research reports as directed by team pipeline and publishing calendarManage direct-to-client distribution channels for published notesMaintain and update research information resourcesWork closely with data analysis team to identify unique data points to support research, while also identifying insightful tables and graphs that can clearly illustrate that informationDevelop and manage relationships with both client and non-client industry professionals to help support primary research effortsManage and respond to inquiries from clients, press, internal colleagues and the general public regarding published researchQualificationsBA/BS in Finance, Business Administration, Economics or Computer Science preferred. Strong understanding of financial concepts such as valuation techniques (DCF, comps, etc.), market sizing, IRRs, asset allocations, fund benchmarks, KPIs etc.3-5+ years’ experience in equity research, investment banking, venture capital, private equity, management consulting or other related financial services roleStrong interest in venture capital and growth equityCritical thinkerDetail oriented / analytical mindsetStrong writing abilityStrong communication skills, both verbal and writtenExcel proficiencyExperience in SQL, PitchBook Platform &/or other financial databases a plusCompany Overview At PitchBook, we provide transparency into the capital markets by organizing the world’s meaningful business information and making it useful to our customers. We work tirelessly to arm global professionals with comprehensive data on the entire venture capital, private equity and M&A landscape—including companies, investors, funds, investments, exits and people—so they can discover and execute opportunities with confidence. Our data and analysis are available through our award-winning flagship product, the PitchBook Platform, as well as our powerful suite of integrated tools, industry news and in-depth reports.  If you are ready to start the conversation about how you might contribute to all the happenings at PitchBook, submit your resume today! PitchBook appreciates and respects diversity, and as such, we are an equal opportunity employer.

Name: Business Intelligence Analyst
Description: About Crowd CowHow many times in your career do you have the chance to create a ubiquitous consumer brand, build an entirely new supply chain, and change a big part of the food system? Crowd Cow is a mission-driven startup founded in 2015 with the idea that the most important of food purchases beef and other proteins deserves to be associated with high-quality practices, total transparency, and close connection to the independent family farms producing the food. The Crowd Cow model isnt the norm: In this country, 84% of beef comes from industrialized and factory processes that dont benefit consumers, small-scale farmers or animals. Today, Crowd Cow offers the most convenient and direct way to purchase from independent and family-owned farms, giving American consumers access to a world of craft beef more diverse and flavorful than most people realize. Were also creating opportunities for the very best independent producers to reach more customers and to showcase their unique traditions in ways never possible via the internet. Crowd Cow has raised significant investment and has been featured in leading publications including the New York Times, the TODAY Show, Food & Wine, Forbes, the Guardian and more.About This RoleAbout this Position: Were looking for someone curious, who feels comfortable asking why? and is who tenacious about discovering the answer. To be successful in this role, youll need the ability to: think analytically, use a wide array of technical skills, clearly communicate your earned insights, and concisely document them for others to learn from. This role has a very broad scope of impact and youll be collaborating with cross-functional teams in several departments. Youll also need to be a self-starter who is comfortable with ambiguity and able to think big (while paying careful attention to the details). At Crowd Cow, were scrappy and growing, so being comfortable working in a fast-paced & dynamic environment is also crucial! The primary focus of this role is to work with our marketing team leaders to define their reporting & analytics needs; then youll design, build, and deploy the necessary instrumentation, data models and reporting structures required to satisfy those requirements. The secondary focus is to support our continuous (and often ad-hoc) analytics initiatives. Some examples include: customer segmentation/profiling, customer lifetime-value (CLV) cohorting and optimization, paid marketing optimization & attribution modeling, merchandising/pricing optimization (just to name a few). Your efforts will directly impact the daily operations of our business and youll have the opportunity to work closely with senior leadership to deeply understand our business and turn insights into action.Youre excited about this role because youll have the opportunity to Gain broad business exposure by directly supporting cross-functional teams from every department Deeply impact critical initiatives through the development of actionable insights Drive the discovery of KPIs and build analytical systems & reports that drive our business forward Analyze & report on key insight trends and build models that predict customer behaviorWere excited about you because Youre a self-starter with a strong ownership and the ability to manage through ambiguity Youre creative & innovative and are excited to bring new ideas to the table You have strong communication skills and people skills Youre energetic and passionate about our mission to create an alternative to factory farmed meatResponsibilities: Manage attribution, analyze performance and identify opportunities in Acquisition channels (i.e., search, display, SEO, marketplaces, and other digital channels) Supporting marketing by building out reporting on channel & site performance, CACs, conversion rates, funnel metrics, etc. Analyze conversion funnel data and identify opportunities to improve ROI, engagement and retention. Name: BUSINESS & DATA ANALYST
Description: BUSINESS & DATA ANALYST  Req #: 162613  Department: UW INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY  Appointing Department Web Address: http://www.washington.edu/uwit/employment/  Job Location: Seattle Campus  Posting Date: 11/29/2018  Closing Info: Open Until Filled  Salary: Commensurate with experience  Shift: First Shift  Notes: If you would like to find out more about what it is like to work for UW-IT, as well as to get a feel for our culture and our people, visit us at our employment website.  As a UW employee, you have a unique opportunity to change lives on our campuses, in our state and around the world. UW employees offer their boundless energy, creative problem solving skills and dedication to build stronger minds and a healthier world. UW faculty and staff also enjoy outstanding benefits, professional growth opportunities and unique resources in an environment noted for diversity, intellectual excitement, artistic pursuits and natural beauty. All of which has allowed the UW to be nationally recognized as a “Great College to Work For” for five consecutive years. The Enterprise Information, Integration & Analytics unit (EIIA) at the University of Washington (UW) provides consistent and reliable architectures, guidelines, standards, tools, and services for analysis, design, integration, management, and delivery of institutional data. In addition, the EIIA group manages, develops and maintains institutional data resources, including the UW Enterprise Data Warehouse (EDW) and UW Enterprise Web Services (EWS), to provide information for decision-making through central business intelligence (BI) products and tools. EIIA is currently seeking a Business and Data Analyst to perform the design of information in the EDW, the EWS, the enterprise integration platform (EIP), and the BI platform. The analyst’s responsibilities include gathering and documenting requirements, developing conceptual data models, producing data linkage specifications, and prototyping data structure and analytics to meet various business requirements. The business and data analyst is a data management professional experienced in business and data analysis, data profiling, data integration and design, information delivery and customer experience delivery. The position requires depth of knowledge and skills in enterprise data management methods, relational and dimensional data modeling, source-to-target mapping, and data modeling tools. The incumbent will possess the full range of knowledge and experience in data warehouse development life-cycle and its processes. The incumbent should be familiar with agile project management method and be able to effectively perform needed role in the agile process. To be successful, the analyst will need to exhibit excellent qualities in attention to detail, analytical acumen, facilitating and communication, collaboration with stakeholders and partners, and competing priority management. The analyst needs to have top communication skills at inter-personal level, and in presentation to large group. The emphasis and focus of this position is on the “global view” of UW institutional data, the supporting data architecture and blue-prints for this big-picture view, and the task to translate big-picture view into detailed implementation. The position is cross-cutting, requiring coordination and liaison to internal team roles as well as external groups to ensure broad data integration and business value for UW. The analyst is expected to collaborate easily and effectively with other data managment and design team members, in particular Information Architects & Data Modelers, other Business Data Analysts (BAs) and members of the data integration teams. This position will also be outward facing to UW campus administrative and academic units for the assessment of critical information needs and for the promotion of standards and best practices in data design and modeling. Requirements: Bachelors degree in Computer Science, Information Management, Library Sciences or equivalent  Minimum of four year experience in Information Management, Data Warehousing and/or Business Intelligence.  Demonstrated experience in business analysis and requirements gathering.  Proficient using SQL for data profiling and data analysis.  Superb technical writing and communication skills.  Outstanding collaboration skills with colleagues at all levels and across different organizations.  Demonstrated ability to work independently and with minimal supervision.  Experience facilitating meetings, constructively addressing input and criticism, and resolving conflicts.  Effectively presents complex technical material to non-technical audiences in an approachable way.  Able to understand and communicate business relevance to management / leadership teams.  Ability to train, mentor, and guide others  Demonstrated excellent written/oral communication skills, technical documentation skills, user liaison skills, and personal interaction abilities. Desired: Strong experience in data modeling and data design, incl. relational and dimensional.  Strong experience with data management / data integration design and implementations.  Experience conducting quality assurance and/or user acceptance testing.  Demonstrated knowledge and work experience with enterprise-wide relational databases, scripting languages, XML, SQL Server, BI reporting tools.  Experience in process and project management in a large volume data environment.  Knowledge of multiple business subject areas, i.e. Finance and Student, etc.  Experience in a major research university setting.  Experience in an Agile software development environment. Conditions:Work in open office environment. Application Process: The application process for UW positions may include completion of a variety of online assessments to obtain additional information that will be used in the evaluation process. These assessments may include Work Authorization, Cover Letter and/or others. Any assessments that you need to complete will appear on your screen as soon as you select “Apply to this position”. Once you begin an assessment, it must be completed at that time; if you do not complete the assessment you will be prompted to do so the next time you access your “My Jobs” page. If you select to take it later, it will appear on your "My Jobs" page to take when you are ready. Please note that your application will not be reviewed, and you will not be considered for this position until all required assessments have been completed. REQUIREMENTS:  See above  The University of Washington is a leader in environmental stewardship & sustainability, and committed to becoming climate neutral. The University of Washington is an equal opportunity, affirmative action employer. To request disability accommodation in the application process, contact the Disability Services Office at 206-543-6450 / 206-543-6452 (tty) or dso@uw.edu. Apply for this job

Name: Treasury Analyst
Description: At Remitly, we help immigrant communities around the world send over $6 billion a year to their loved ones. Sending money is faster, easier, and costs less with our all-digital money transfer platform. Our vision is to transform the lives of immigrants and their families by providing the most trusted financial service products on the planet. At Remitly, your work has a direct and positive impact on people around the globe. Your work matters, every day.  The treasury team is a core part of Remitly's business, as it is tied to both revenue generation and risk mitigation. The mission of the team is to empower Remitly to provide exceptional service and value to our customers by putting money in the right place at the right time with uncompromising financial efficiency. The five core tenets of the team include: deliver on customer promises, mitigate risks, maximize FX revenue, optimize the use of working capital, and achieve operational excellence with scale. The treasury team works very closely with several other functions, including the pricing team who is tasked with setting the price (FX rate and fees charged) for each product, the business development team who negotiates the relationships with international banks and disbursement partners, compliance, and accounting.  The ideal candidate will possess the skills and experience needed to significantly contribute to our ongoing efforts to build and deploy a secure, scalable and robust global treasury operations platform. This position plays a critical role in meeting our customer promise while safeguarding customer and corporate assets. It is essential that the candidate be organized, detail-oriented and reliable. Key Responsibilities:Effectively manage daily global funding activity including timely execution of funding analysis, trades and resolution of funding issuesContribute to enhanced foreign currency revenue optimization and fx risk management effortsOversee deployment, implementation and execution of funding and trading models on a global basisPartner with the engineering and data teams in support of the development and rollout of a robust global treasury platformAnalysis and reporting of treasury activity and performanceIncorporate global business expansions into daily funding processesManage regulatory liquidity ratiosOversee borrowing and repayment of line of credit and corporate fundsCreate processes and procedures to hand off key treasury data across multiple time zonesPreferred Qualifications:Strong applicable industry experience: We're looking for a candidate with meaningful treasury and cash management experience within a multinational corporation. The ideal candidate will have worked within a "best in class" organization, allowing him/her to assist in identifying and implementing enhanced treasury processes and solutionsA team approach to solving problems: Building a global treasury platform will require collaboration across the organizationAn entrepreneurial conviction: We're looking for someone who is able to drive change and innovation while delivering on core departmental responsibilitiesStrong Excel skills required (VBA and SQL experience highly desirable)Prior experience in FX and FX risk management is highly desirablePrior experience in cash forecasting is desirableBachelor's degree in a quantitative discipline (Finance, Economics, Statistics, etc.). Master's degree, CTP or CFA designation a plus Remitly is an independent digital remittance company that transfers over $6 billion in annualized volume through its proprietary global money transfer network across Africa, Asia, Central, and South America. Its reliable and easy-to-use mobile app makes the process of sending money faster, easier, more transparent and less costly by eliminating the forms, codes, agents, extra time and fees typical of the traditional, century-old money transfer process. Remitly is backed by industry-leading investors, World Bank's International Finance Corporation (IFC), Naspers' PayU, Silicon Valley Bank, Stripes Group, DFJ, DN Capital, QED Investors, Trilogy Equity Partners, Bezos Expeditions, Founders' Co-Op, and TomorrowVentures. The company is headquartered in Seattle, with additional offices in London, the Philippines, and Nicaragua. For more information, visit remitly.com. Remitly is an Equal Opportunity Employer. Individuals seeking employment at Remitly are considered without regard to race, color, religion, national origin, age, sex, marital status, ancestry, physical or mental disability, veteran status, or sexual orientation. Remitly is an eVerify Employer.

As part of the Analytics Consulting group, the Business Intelligence (BI) Business Analyst (‘BI Analyst’) is responsible for working with internal customers to define and prioritize business requirements; partnering with development, application, and other Analyst teams to design and implement analytics solutions; and providing an overall excellent customer experience. While all members of the Analytics Consulting group are expected to develop proficiency across all domains we support, this position will focus heavily on: Access management process oversight and implementation for Analytics solutions;Service request (ticket) management and triage;Identifying and implementing internal process improvement within Analytics;Complex business requirements gathering and management. This position regularly works with end-users, management, and other Analyst groups across UW Medicine, to identify business problems and opportunities for process improvement, as well as supports the overall quality of enterprise data. The incumbent produces thorough analyses and detailed business and technical requirements documentation as necessary to support solution development; works closely with Programmers, Application owners, Data Architects, and Solution Architects to ensure that solutions meet customer needs, and strives to support the voice of the customer in all interactions. The BI Analyst stays connected to the customer throughout the lifecycle of their request(s) and ensures all solutions undergo effective quality review and user acceptance testing. The BI Analyst also assists in release documentation, user training, and ongoing support.  The BI Analyst has a unique focus on driving ongoing process improvement and consolidation of the access management and service request processes for the Analytics Consulting group. The incumbent identifies, implements, and measures opportunities to improve how the Analytics Consulting group receives requests for work, and provides access to data and reporting solutions; ensures service-level expectations are measured and met across all Analytics teams; and engages with internal customers and data governance groups to make certain processes are easy to use, effective, and fully compliant with enterprise policies governing access.  As a member of the Analytics Consulting group the BI Analyst directly supports the triage of incoming customer requests with other team members; works broadly across the Analytics Consulting group to ensure effective work prioritization; and ensures requests are assigned to the best possible resource(s). The BI Analyst engages with other team members to drive process improvement within the Analytics Consulting group and throughout the department as a whole. The incumbent stays up-to-date on all department solutions and services and frequently demonstrates and educates customers on existing and new tools.  This position is expected to leverage enterprise business intelligence tools to answer questions about data, produce meaningful analyses, and independently create reports, dashboards, and other data visualizations when needed. The incumbent should exhibit:Strong analytical abilities partnered with effective summarization skills.Skill at readily manipulating large data sets to produce actionable information and visual analytics.The ability to work collectively with other team members, as well as one-on-one, to effectively deliver on agreed upon tasks.A clear pattern of excellent communication and writing for both technical and non-technical audiences.The ability to plan and manage the work of others without direct authority.A critical eye for detail in his/her own work as well as in that of team members.The ability to quickly triage complicated tasks and identify next steps.Understanding of core principles of data governance, quality, and security.Proficiency with independent projects as well as with effective team collaboration.Willingness to learn new skills with the ability to adapt existing knowledge in order to tackle new challenges.A strong customer focus that is apparent in how he/she solves problems. This position requires independent judgment and collaboration with both internal and external partners to proactively manage, analyze, report, and implement the Analytics programs, projects and tasks assigned. This role will work across cross-functional teams. This position will also require the ability to navigate complex levels of the UW Medicine environment in addition to working with managers and directors of UW Medicine entities. The incumbent is expected to perform analytical work requiring knowledge of administrative principles and analytical practices. The position will be provided access to restricted or confidential information including: employee and patient information, medical center strategic plans and initiatives, financial information (or other sensitive materials and information). The BI Analyst will be required to maintain confidentiality and follow strict compliance and organizational guidelines.  The Analytics Consulting group has a dual report into ITS and the UW School of Medicine; provides operational oversight for the major analytics platforms and tools at UW Medicine; and is a key support function as UW Medicine transitions towards value based health care. The BI Analyst collaborates effectively with colleagues and other departments at Harborview Medical Center, Northwest Hospital & Medical Center, Valley Medical Center, UW Medical Center, UW Neighborhood Clinics, UW Physicians, UW School of Medicine, and ITS, as well as with other Project Managers, Technology Managers, and Directors. investigation, analysis, review, and documentation of all or part of a business in terms of business functions and data needs.Manages the requirements development process through the elicitation, analysis, specification, and verification of multiple levels of requirements (i.e., business, stakeholder, and/or solution).Supports the ongoing management of business requirements.Creates viable and consumable specifications, including acceptance criteria, in preparation for the sign-off, construction, and testing of reporting solutions.Project Management and Process Improvement (20%)Utilizes Name: Sr. Business Analyst - Metrics and Reporting
Description: External Job Description  AWS Worldwide Commercial Sales Operations team is seeking a Business Analyst with broad technical skills, strong financial acumen and a deep analytical background to assist the Commercials Sales Operations team in creating efficiencies, assessing performance and reporting & delivering results. As a member of this team, you will leverage strong data extraction skills to drive worldwide reporting deliverables, create ad hoc financial and sales performance analysis, support business planning, and implement ideas for process improvement. The individual must have the ability to communicate effectively across multiple technical and non-technical business units, as well as across other geographies. Successful members of this team collaborate effectively to solve data problems, implement new reporting solutions, and deliver successfully against high operational standards. The ideal candidate will be a highly motivated individual that seeks to tell the story of the data with little direction or supervision.  Key responsibilities include, but are not limited to:  Support the development of continuously-evolving forecast models and methodologies, owning the quantitative analysis of the performance of our sales team, customers, prospects, partners, markets, and products/services.  · Develop a deep understanding of sales metrics, reporting tools, and data structure in order to identify and drive resolution of issues, provide actionable intelligence with existing metrics or identify, develop, and propose new metrics, dashboards, scorecards or new tools  · Develop relationships and processes with sales, finance, HR, sales operations, and other functional teams to identify and address reporting issues.  · Manage and develop financial tools or reports that align, and simplify, monthly business reviews, annual planning, and forecasting processes  · Create WW financial and operational templates and processes to compile and standardize disparate information that drive standardized reporting and metrics tracking  · Work with regional teams to deconstruct issues and develop solutions that help meet financial and operational goals  · Generate ad hoc and monthly recurring financial and operational performance analysis, based on the needs of the stakeholders  · Provide recommendations through ad hoc data retrieval and analysis from data management systems  · Create new tools and business processes that simplifies, standardizes and enables operational excellence

Name: AWS Partner SFDC Business Analyst
Description: Amazon Web Services (AWS) provides companies of all sizes with an infrastructure web services platform in the cloud (cloud computing). With AWS you can requisition compute power, storage, and many other services gaining access to a suite of elastic IT infrastructure services as your business demands them. AWS is the leading platform for designing and developing applications for the cloud and is growing rapidly with hundreds of thousands of companies in over 190 countries on the platform.  AWS growth is driving a rapid expansion of its world-wide sales team and the need for an experienced Salesforce.com (SFDC) Business Analyst to help us define and implement enhancements to existing or new capabilities/functionality for our business customers. You will own the relationship with our business owners to ensure their requirements are clearly captured, documented and communicated utilizing existing agile and waterfall processes. As part of the AWS Global Business Operations (GBO) team you will work globally with business groups at all levels to understand strategy, requirements and timelines, and map those to CRM platform objectives. The primary tasks are understanding business needs for knowledge delivery, translating them into user stories, assessing and analyzing problem domain using available data and information, proposing and documenting solutions, testing final product against original requirements, and helping with rollout and change management efforts.  The successful candidate must be a self-starter, be able to manage multiple tasks and projects simultaneously, own deliverables end to end, prioritize workload effectively, and thrive in a dynamic environment. They will be passionate about their work, self-motivated, detail oriented and have excellent problem solving abilities. This individual must also work well under pressure to meet ongoing and overlapping deadlines within short time constraints. They will have superb communication skills and will be able to communicate complex analytical results, both written and verbally, in a clear and easy-to-understand way. They will deal with ambiguous problems, work with Project Managers and/or Developers on finding solutions, and will drive towards simple solutions to complex problems.  AWS is home to the largest Salesforce.com instance at Amazon. We use the collective experience of our rapidly growing SFDC team to solve challenging problems. Of course we use the Sales and Marketing Clouds, but we are also building custom solutions for business development, operations, partners, contracts, and a lot more. Come help us build with the worlds leading CRM at one of the worlds largest companies, where every day is still day one.  Key Responsibilities Requirements Coordinate the collection of business requirements, user acceptance test (UAT) plans and use casesDeliver technology solutions partner and consult with the business to identify and define business requirements and to initiate and prioritize enhancement, gap analysis, and prepare user storiesDevelop support model provide production support for business owned rules, processes, and maintain themSubject matter expert develop deep knowledge of the AWS GBO Salesforce platform and how it supports downstream/upstream systems utilized by AWS, advise the business on best practices and requirements for optimizing the use of these systemsSeek out ways to utilize SFDC to improve processes and productivity, and make recommendations to support an organization scaling at a rapid paceManage a release process to test, validate and implement new applications/code, and updates to existing applications/code that support key business groupsWork with various functions and end users to identify, document, and communicate standard business processes as they relate to SalesforceHands on SFDC configuration and data migration experience to execute on projects

Name: Sr. Business Analyst, Seller Experience
Description: At Amazon.com we're working to be the most customer-centric company on earth. To get there, we need exceptionally talented, bright, and driven people. In Seller Support we are building and operating exceptional solutions to provide world class support to Sellers on Amazon's Marketplace business, which exceeds 45% of the total Amazon.com platform sales and growing. If you'd like to help us build the place to find and buy anything online, this is your chance to make history as a Business Analyst for the Seller Experience team based in Seattle.  Are you data savvy, business focused, with a desire to use your analytical prowess to help others understand Seller needs and drive change through rigorous data analysis?  The successful candidate will be highly analytical, an expert with SQL and Excel, experienced with significance testing and A/B experimentation, resourceful, customer focused, team oriented, and have an ability to work independently under time constraints to meet deadlines. In this role you will: · Be an important member of a team that improves the experience of selling on Amazon by eliminating defects, proactively identifying and resolving selling issues, and discovering seller insights.  · These objectives by diving deep into Amazons data lake to reveal trends, support machine-learning based automation, poll sellers and analyze how sentiments predict behaviors, perform cohort analysis, and run experiments to test hypotheses and to quantify impacts.  · Work closely with product managers, SDEs, Technical Product Managers, data engineers, process engineers and senior management to define and build reporting and analytic solutions that allow us to make data-based product and business decisions that make it easier to sell on Amazon.  · Enable effective decision making by retrieving and aggregating data from multiple sources and compiling it into a digestible and actionable format.  · Analyze and solve business problems with focus on understanding root causes and discovering forward-looking opportunities.  · Rigorously examine metrics and design new metrics that provide guidance about the state of the business.  · Communicate complex analyses and insights to stakeholders and business leaders, both verbally and in writing.  · Create and maintain tools and reports which support Senior leadership and various teams throughout the organization.  Amazon.com is an Equal Opportunity-Affirmative Action Employer Minority / Female / Disability / Veteran / Gender Identity / Sexual Orientation.

Name: WORKFORCE MANAGEMENT SYSTEMS BUSINESS ANALYST
Description: WORKFORCE MANAGEMENT SYSTEMS BUSINESS ANALYST Req #: 161708 Department: UW MEDICINE HUMAN RESOURCES Job Location Detail: UW Tower Posting Date: 11/19/2018 Closing Info: Open Until Filled Salary: Salary is commensurate with experience and education. Shift: First Shift Notes: As a UW employee, you will enjoy generous benefits and work/life programs. For detailed information on Benefits for this position, click here. UW Medicine provides outstanding care to patients from around the globe, educates the next generation of physicians and scientists, and supports one of the world’s largest and most comprehensive medical research programs. UW Medicine’s four hospitals – Harborview Medical Center, Northwest Hospital & Medical Center, University of Washington Medical Center and Valley Medical Center – admit more than 63,000 patients each year. UW Medicine provides outpatient care for more than 1.3 million patients each year at its 12 UW Neighborhood Clinics and its many other primary and specialty care clinics.  The Human Resources department's mission is to support UW faculty and staff in successfully meeting the goals of the University by providing high quality and responsive human resources support to foster an exceptional work environment that encourages, nurtures and recognizes the professional development of University employees. The department's vision is to create a premier HR organization whose staff members are dedicated to the goal of working together to provide the highest possible quality of services in carrying out its mission. UW Medicine Human Resources has an outstanding full time opportunity for a Workforce Management Systems (WMS) Business Analyst. The WMS Business Analyst will primarily support the data migration, documentation and validation efforts for the implementation of the HR / Payroll business and system changes associated with the integration of Northwest Hospital (NWH) and University of Washington Physicians (UWP) into UW Medicine. The WMS Business Analyst will play a key role in documenting the scope of data to be migrated, conducting field-level data mapping, supporting the design of a systematic and repeatable method for converting the data, as well as the the activities required to extract, transform, load, and validate the data. The WMS Business Analyst will be a critical resource on the team for ensuring the complete , timely and accurate migration of NWH and UWP integration data into UW Medicine. POSITION COMPLEXITIES: The WMS Business Analyst will support data migration, documentation and analysis for the NWH/UWP HR & Labor project. In addition, this position requires the ability to work as part of a larger project team that consists of resources from various organizations and departments at UW, NWH and UWP. Additional responsibilities include supporting the WMS team by assisting in the maintenance of the team’s work plan, coordinating with team members to ensure project tasks are completed on time, documenting inputs provided by Subject Matter Experts (SMEs), scheduling meetings & capturing follow-ups, as well as contributing to team deliverables (Data Load Schedule, Data Validation Plan, Test Plan, Process Documentation, Training Materials, etc). POSITION DIMENSIONS AND IMPACT TO THE UNIVERSITY: The WMS Business Analyst will work closely with NWH, UWP and existing UW and UW Medicine HR and Payroll teams, other key stakeholders, and project team members throughout the project. The position will report directly to the Director of WMS. RESPONSIBILITIES:Coordinate and facilitate meetings between the various organizational stakeholders to determine data migration requirements, including definition of scope and data sources.Identify gaps in the data available and be part of recommending next steps & actions to close gaps; track issues to resolution.Conduct field-by-field analysis of NWH and UWP data to be converted into UW systems by collecting & organizing inputs from Subject Matter Experts (SMEs); track follow up tasks and actions through to resolution.Produce a pair of complete data dictionary deliverables (NWH & UWP), mapping the NWH and UWP data to the UW required data fields in Workday. Keep data dictionary in synch with data templates that are updated at least twice annually. Ensure that refinements in UW production data definitions are synched up with the data dictionaries.Ensure requisite business owners and subject matter experts at NWH, UWP, and UW have the opportunity to provide input to the field-by-field data mapping and analysis, leveraging their subject matter expertise to review and approve the analysis, making the best use of their time.Partner with technical resources to support the design of a systematic and repeatable method for extracting and transforming NWH and UWP data into the readily loadable format needed for use by UW systems. This will include supporting multiple test loads and unit & end to end level validations. Coordinate & document the review and validation efforts of NWH and UWP subject matter experts.Maintain the WMS Team Work Plan and prepare status reports.Coordinate with WMS team members to ensure that tasks are completed timely.Assist in tracking issues to resolution, escalating where necessary.Contribute to the team deliverables (Data Load Schedule, Data Validation Plan, Test Plan, Process Documentation, Training Materials, etc). REQUIREMENTS:BA +5 years of relevant experience, equivalent experience can substitute for degreeExperience working with complex data, and organizing data into standard formatsProficiency with Microsoft Excel, Word, PowerPoint, e-mail and electronic calendaring systemsFamiliarity with VisioExceptional communication skills – both written and verbalExcellent active listening skillsAbility to clearly articulate complex messages to a variety of audiencesAbility to establish and maintain strong relationshipsAbility to quickly develop trustAbility to influence others and move toward a common vision or goalAble to work effectively at all levels in an organizationAbility to work collaboratively with and through othersComfort in working with new technologies and software to gather and report information.Sense of humor and willingness to assume best intentionsFlexible and adaptable; able to work in ambiguous situations as well as with multiple competing prioritiesOrganized with a natural inclination for processes and systemsCritical thinking, problem solving and root cause identification skillsHigh degree of attention to detailAcute business acumen and ability to analyze, model, and interpret dataAbility to receive critical feedback, adapt and adjustFamiliarity with project management & coordination approaches, tools and phases of the project lifecycleExperience with medium to large-scale organizational changes and system implementations, and willingness to share insights based on experience CONDITIONS OF EMPLOYMENT:This position is funded through the end of the project which is anticipated to be the end of February 2020.Application Process: The application process for UW positions may include completion of a variety of online assessments to obtain additional information that will be used in the evaluation process. These assessments may include Work Authorization, Cover Letter and/or others. Any assessments that you need to complete will appear on your screen as soon as you select “Apply to this position”. If you select to take it later, it will appear on your "My Jobs" page to take when you are ready. Name: Senior Bi Business Analyst
Description: As a UW employee, you will enjoy generous benefits and work/life programs.  For detailed information on Benefits for this position, click here. As a UW employee, you have a unique opportunity to change lives on our campuses, in our state and around the world. UW employees offer their boundless energy, creative problem solving skills and dedication to build stronger minds and a healthier world.  UW faculty and staff also enjoy outstanding benefits, professional growth opportunities and unique resources in an environment noted for diversity, intellectual excitement, artistic pursuits and natural beauty. All of which has allowed the UW to be nationally recognized as a "Great College to Work For" for five consecutive years.  The School of Medicine (SOM) has an outstanding opportunity for a Senior BI Business Analyst.  The Operations and Financial Reporting Department, Office of the Dean, provides financial oversight and analysis of the Dean's Office departments as well as academic departments' financial activities within the SOM. Under the general direction of the Director for Departmental Computing, the Senior BI Business Analyst serves as a flexible resource that works independently to examine and analyze administrative systems, fiscal and/or administrative records, and institutional practices. The Senior BI Business Analyst reports to management on results, provides impact assessments, and recommends training and improvement in operations and information systems. This position has a wide range of responsibilities to include requirement gathering for projects, acting as the point of contact for SOM clients, financial reporting and analysis, operational assessments, and documenting projects, systems, and processes. This position acts in an advisory capacity to senior management in the School providing research and analytical support on data and reporting issues. Must demonstrate effective project management analysis and sound business judgment.  Interpreting, analyzing and disseminating rules, policies and procedures, as well as ensuring staffs' accurate understanding and application, is critical. This position must provide technical expertise in the integration of financial information from several sources (UW Financial Accounting System (FAS), School of Medicine department shadow systems, University of Washington Medical Center, Harborview Medical Center, as well as affiliates such as Seattle Children's Hospital and the Fred Hutchinson Cancer Research Center). This position must determine which data is necessary, the source of the data and the most efficient method for obtaining the data and converting to a format consistent with the Academic Medical Center reporting requirements. It will be necessary to make theoretical or subjective judgments with respect to compatibility of data between different organizations (i.e. mapping of financial statement interfaces between organizations). New approaches, methods or techniques will be required to align School of Medicine departments and outside organizations' processes to provide information necessary for consolidated financial statements.  Business Analysis  Apply user centered design practices, interview stakeholders and system users to determine functional requirements for new and existing systems. Facilitate discussions with stakeholders and subject matter experts to research and analyze the end-users needs. Create documentation to support understanding of business needs and document the project requirements.  Identify, develop and evaluate solutions encompassing a variety of automated and manual techniques, considering programming complexity, on-going technical support requirements and department end user workflow where applicable.  Review new or modified program, including documentation, diagram, and flowchart, to determine if program will perform according to user request and conform to guidelines. Create project documentation as necessary in support of agile development techniques.  Analyze information systems, data base models and/or interface needs. Evaluate information gathered from multiple sources and ensure accuracy and completion of the data. Partner with developers to test and validate the data.  Write, revise, and verify quality standards and test procedures for program design and product evaluation to attain quality of software. Work with the users to test the requested changes and document the results. Provide trainings and presentations on new products/features, as needed.  Provide support with analytical, design, and development tasks associated with the implementation of information system solutions.  Provide on-going support to clients by correlating user needs with information system design and communicate with the department's developers  Help prioritize, troubleshoot, and resolve system and service problems, in order to provide very reliable and highly available computing services.  Collect and assemble data needed for various SOM surveys.  Project Management  Serve in a project management capacity over low to moderately complex projects. Work with formal and informal project plans, and work independently or in a group to meet deadlines.  Identify appropriate level of oversight and resource requirements, facilitate team member activities and communicate project progress with management, developers, customers, and users.  Use solid judgment to determine appropriate escalation and resolution of issues within project structure. Work with management to evaluate and communicate business issues and impact.  Help managing competing stakeholder priorities and assist in identifying best approach to meet expected deadlines.  Other Related Duties as Assigned  Complete special projects for the dean and executive leadership.  Develop cross-training for staff on reporting, databases, and external resources. REQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS Bachelors Degress in Accounting, Business Adminstration, Computer Science or related field or equivalent education/experience.  6-8 years experience.  Experience in data and process modeling.  Experience in relational database applications such as MS SQL and Access.  Demonstrated ability to develop creative solutions for complex financial reporting situations.  Demonstrated experience working in large, highly structured environments.  Proven leadership and strong communication skills (end-user orientation).  Ability to work independently with a high degree of reliability, accuracy and productivity.  Ability to create accurate, cogent reports.  Proficiency with various computer programs and databases.  Excellent communication skills, demonstrating diplomacy and tact. DESIRED Proficient in SQL and VB Scripting, MS Access, Crystal and MS SQL Reporting Services.  Knowledge of University of Washington financial systems.  Experience with academic medical center financial reporting.  Recent experience with financial reporting applications (such as general ledger) conversion or installation. CONDITIONS OF EMPLOYMENT The application process for UW positions may include completion of a variety of online assessments to obtain additional information that will be used in the evaluation process. These assessments may include Work Authorization, Cover Letter and/or others. Any assessments that you need to complete will appear on your screen as soon as you select "Apply to this position". Once you begin an assessment, it must be completed at that time; if you do not complete the assessment you will be prompted to do so the next time you access your "My Jobs" page. If you select to take it later, it will appear on your "My Jobs" page to take when you are ready. Please note that your application will not be reviewed, and you will not be considered for this position until all required assessments have been completed.SDL2017

Name: Business Analyst- Seller Payments
Description: As one of the largest e-commerce companies in the world, Amazon processes billions of secure on-line transactions via a number of payment mechanisms, including credit cards, direct debit and electronic gift certificates. Transactions are processed on behalf of thousands of merchants, including Amazon.com. Amazon is known across the globe as the most trusted company on the Internet. We are committed to delivering an exceptional customer experience.  The Payments Services owns and maintains the software which processes 20+ payment methods worldwide. The Business Operations Team supports the larger Payments Services organization which includes software development, product management and technical operations. The Business Operations team is the first contact for payment transactional issues, receiving escalations from internal clients such as Customer Service, Finance, Accounting and Fraud as well as third party partners and banks relied upon to process payments. Additionally this team is responsible for driving operational efficiencies and escalation reduction opportunities. This team also manages the operational relationship with third party payment partners, advocating for customer experience and driving operational improvements.  The Payments Business Analyst is responsible for driving operational excellence within the payments space. In this role you will identify and drive to resolution payments issues impacting customers on a global scale. You will work to identify, execute, and drive projects with internal and external business partners to improve the Customer and Seller Payments Experience across Amazon. You will collaborate with teams across Amazon to improve business processes to increase operational efficiencies.  The ideal candidate is a motivated self-starter that can work independently in a fast paced, ambiguous environment with limited supervision. He or she must be a fast learner, who can quickly absorb the nuances of Amazon's varied payment offerings as well as the behavior of Amazon's internal systems. He or she will be analytical in their decision making, with a demonstrated ability to drive issues to completion. Primary Responsibilities: · Work in a deep area of coverage, routinely working on issues ranging from small to large number of customers impacted and driving root cause resolution with engineering teams and/or external partners.  · Manage operational workflows working with internal business teams in small to medium sized geographies or products.  · Identify and drive continuous improvement activities.  · Serves as escalation point for program / project team members. Owns, tracks, or escalates issues to ensure that they are addressed, documented, and resolved.  · Displays energy and initiative in solving problems. Will follow all possible avenues to get the job done, are proactive.  · Work requires creativity and judgment. Responsibilities include both routine and non-routine in nature and vary from day to day.  · Identify and evaluate potential risks/obstacles with minimal direction from program managers. Consult, determine, and execute appropriate corrective action.  · Proactively drive customer experience and operational excellence for payment methods used by Amazon customers.  · Successfully build business requirements that technical teams use to implement projects you sponsor.
