Name: Digital Analyst - Business Intelligence
Description: Job #44008Accelerate Your CareerDrive global technologyWith more than $2 billion in revenues, CDK Global is a leading global provider of integrated information technology and digital marketing solutions to the automotive retail and adjacent industries. Focused on enabling end-to-end automotive commerce, CDK provides solutions to dealers in more than 100 countries around the world, serving approximately 28,000 retail locations and most automotive manufacturers. CDK Global solutions automate and integrate critical processes from pre-sale targeted advertising to the sale, financing, insurance, parts supply, repair and maintenance of vehicles, with an increasing focus on utilizing data analytics and predictive intelligence. We’re large enough to make a difference but small enough for your voice to be heard. This means that we are an organization where every person matters. You can make an impact on the success of our business and that of our customers regardless of what career you decide to pursue.From data scientists to sales and client service experts, we’re hiring to support your growth and ours - Green light your career. CDK Global is hiring a  BI Analyst!THE IDEAL CANDIDATE WILL POSSESS: . A background in web analytics or online advertising. . Prior experience in an advertising agency preferred. . Strong experience with SQL and Google Analytics PRINCIPLE DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES:CDK Digital Marketing is seeking a BI Data Analyst who will help guide stakeholders through the process of designing data solutions for clients, while having the technical skills to build and implement those solutions through our Enterprise Data Warehouse. The successful candidate will be able to think strategically about business issues and will have a strong command of data warehousing platforms, reporting automation, data visualization, digital marketing analytics and basic statistics. In addition to these technical skills, we are looking for someone who is comfortable working directly with stakeholders to understand their concerns, use data to address them, and present the results to a non-technical audience in a clear and concise manner. Candidates with a history of owning data driven projects and overcoming obstacles are desired. The BI Data Analyst will be able to take direction, but will also pro-actively drive projects to completion.A comfortable relationship with various flavors of SQL and experience with a fact/dimension based Data Warehouse is essential. Knowledge of “Big” data platforms such as Hadoop, and any experience automating data workflows is a plus. Extracted data will be manipulated, merged, and analyzed to produce reports, graphs, dashboards and other output to ultimately reveal performance of our products for internal and external users. A history of delivering “actionable insights” to stakeholders is desired; CDK is looking for Analysts who want to go beyond reporting.CDK’s Agency Insights Team wants people who are curious about data. The ideal candidate is not intimidated by large and complex data sets and is naturally inclined to view things from an analytical perspective. Industry experience and knowledge of current data visualization and warehousing trends is encouraged. The successful candidate will work closely with OEM Consultants, BI Engineers and other Data Analysts. KNOWLEDGE, SKILLS AND ABILITIES:. BA/BS in a business or technical field; an Advanced Degree is a plus. 3+ years’ experience in a Data Analyst role. Must have experience with Google Analytics and SQL. Experience with Tableau a plus. Experience with Data Warehousing platforms (Oracle, SQL Server, etc.). Experience with websites and digital media analytics. Strong MS Excel and Database skills. Experience with digital marketing concepts, cookies (1st & 3rd party), pixel tags, privacy standards, SEO, social media, advertising attribution methods & models. Demonstrated ability to communicate technical topics to non-technical audiences. Experience with Hadoop, Spark, Hive, Pig, MongoDB or other big data technologies a plus. Automotive vertical experience a plusESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS:. Communicate with business consultants, agency partners and enterprise sales to gather and understand requirements. Ability to manage a backlog, establish priorities, multi-task and work proactively and independently. Data mining from data warehouse, using SQL, RegEx, json, pixel logs, and other big data formats. Analyze web analytics and other quantitative and qualitative data. Data discovery and data cleansingCDK Global knows you have passions outside of work. You have family, friends, sporting events, and lots of things going on. That’s why we offer a comprehensive benefits package to not only take care of you but your family as well. All of our benefits are effective the first day of employment including 401K matching, paid time off to re-energize, donate your time to volunteer in your community, and tuition reimbursement to name a few.At CDK, we pride ourselves on having a diverse workforce. We value and celebrate the uniqueness of individuals and the different perspectives they provide. We offer equal opportunity employment regardless of race, color, religion, gender, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, genetics, disability status, age, marital status, or protected veteran status.

Name: BI BUSINESS ANALYST
Description: BI Business Analyst  Req #: 162086  Department: UW MEDICINE IT SERVICES  Job Location Detail: Work location is at the IBM Building on 5th & Seneca in downtown Seattle  Posting Date: 11/07/2018  Closing Info: Open Until Filled  Salary: Salary commensurate with education and experience.  Shift: First Shift  UW Medicine’s IT Services department is looking for an outstanding BI Business Analyst to join the team! What are we looking for?Patients Are First focus Customer service mindset Interpersonal skills and teamwork Results-oriented attitude Commitment Adaptability and flexibilityWhat are the perks?Medical insurance at reasonable rates with TEN plans to choose from! Dental Insurance at no cost to you OR your dependents…AND we have three plans for you to choose from! 10 paid holidays annually! 1 personal holiday every year! Generous amounts of vacation and sick leave that you can feel good about taking (more than 5 work weeks in your first year) ! TWO Retirement plans to choose from – one even matches 100% of your contributions with immediate vesting! Voluntary Investment program to save more towards your retirement! Deferred Compensation program to save even MORE towards your retirement! Flexible Spending Account...Tax Exempt! Dependent Care Assistance program! On-site Childcare Centers! Long Term Disability insurance! Life and Accidental Death and Dismemberment insurance! U-PASS transportation program and discounted parking…PRE-TAX! Tuition Exemption program – at the UW (and other colleges around the state)! Housing resources and home buying options! Auto, home, renter, and boat group insurance! Valuable membership and merchandise discounts! Federal student loan forgiveness under the Public Service Loan Forgiveness (PSLF) program!For all of the specific details on these benefits and more, please click here.As part of the Analytics Consulting group, the Business Intelligence (BI) Business Analyst (‘BI Analyst’) is responsible for working with internal customers to define and prioritize business requirements; partnering with development, application, and other Analyst teams to design and implement analytics solutions; and providing an overall excellent customer experience. While all members of the Analytics Consulting group are expected to develop proficiency across all domains we support, this position will focus heavily on: Access management process oversight and implementation for Analytics solutions; Service request (ticket) management and triage; Identifying and implementing internal process improvement within Analytics; Complex business requirements gathering and management.This position regularly works with end-users, management, and other Analyst groups across UW Medicine, to identify business problems and opportunities for process improvement, as well as supports the overall quality of enterprise data. The incumbent produces thorough analyses and detailed business and technical requirements documentation as necessary to support solution development; works closely with Programmers, Application owners, Data Architects, and Solution Architects to ensure that solutions meet customer needs, and strives to support the voice of the customer in all interactions. The BI Analyst stays connected to the customer throughout the lifecycle of their request(s) and ensures all solutions undergo effective quality review and user acceptance testing. The BI Analyst also assists in release documentation, user training, and ongoing support. The BI Analyst has a unique focus on driving ongoing process improvement and consolidation of the access management and service request processes for the Analytics Consulting group. The incumbent identifies, implements, and measures opportunities to improve how the Analytics Consulting group receives requests for work, and provides access to data and reporting solutions; ensures service-level expectations are measured and met across all Analytics teams; and engages with internal customers and data governance groups to make certain processes are easy to use, effective, and fully compliant with enterprise policies governing access. As a member of the Analytics Consulting group the BI Analyst directly supports the triage of incoming customer requests with other team members; works broadly across the Analytics Consulting group to ensure effective work prioritization; and ensures requests are assigned to the best possible resource(s). The BI Analyst engages with other team members to drive process improvement within the Analytics Consulting group and throughout the department as a whole. The incumbent stays up-to-date on all department solutions and services and frequently demonstrates and educates customers on existing and new tools. This position is expected to leverage enterprise business intelligence tools to answer questions about data, produce meaningful analyses, and independently create reports, dashboards, and other data visualizations when needed. The incumbent should exhibit: Strong analytical abilities partnered with effective summarization skills. Skill at readily manipulating large data sets to produce actionable information and visual analytics. The ability to work collectively with other team members, as well as one-on-one, to effectively deliver on agreed upon tasks. A clear pattern of excellent communication and writing for both technical and non-technical audiences. The ability to plan and manage the work of others without direct authority. A critical eye for detail in his/her own work as well as in that of team members. The ability to quickly triage complicated tasks and identify next steps. Understanding of core principles of data governance, quality, and security. Proficiency with independent projects as well as with effective team collaboration. Willingness to learn new skills with the ability to adapt existing knowledge in order to tackle new challenges. A strong customer focus that is apparent in how he/she solves problems.This position requires independent judgment and collaboration with both internal and external partners to proactively manage, analyze, report, and implement the Analytics programs, projects and tasks assigned. This role will work across cross-functional teams. This position will also require the ability to navigate complex levels of the UW Medicine environment in addition to working with managers and directors of UW Medicine entities. The incumbent is expected to perform analytical work requiring knowledge of administrative principles and analytical practices. The position will be provided access to restricted or confidential information including: employee and patient information, medical center strategic plans and initiatives, financial information (or other sensitive materials and information). The BI Analyst will be required to maintain confidentiality and follow strict compliance and organizational guidelines. The Analytics Consulting group has a dual report into ITS and the UW School of Medicine; provides operational oversight for the major analytics platforms and tools at UW Medicine; and is a key support function as UW Medicine transitions towards value based health care. The BI Analyst collaborates effectively with colleagues and other departments at Harborview Medical Center, Northwest Hospital & Medical Center, Valley Medical Center, UW Medical Center, UW Neighborhood Clinics, UW Physicians, UW School of Medicine, and ITS, as well as with other Project Managers, Technology Managers, and Directors. Responsibilities include:Requirements Gathering and Verification (60%)Collaborates with UW Medicine partners and BI Report Developers facilitating business requirements analysis via the methodical investigation, analysis, review, and documentation of all or part of a business in terms of business functions and data needs. Manages the requirements development process through the elicitation, analysis, specification, and verification of multiple levels of requirements (i.e., business, stakeholder, and/or solution). Supports the ongoing management of business requirements. Creates viable and consumable specifications, including acceptance criteria, in preparation for the sign-off, construction, and testing of reporting solutions.Project Management and Process Improvement (20%)Utilizes industry best practices for gathering and documenting end users’ reporting requirements. Coordinates with Data Architects, SQL administrators, BI administrators and others to understand and document technical requirements, capabilities, and limitations. Collaborates with Data Architects, SQL Administrators, BI administrators, and others to design appropriate BI solutions based on business and technical requirements. Translates high level business requirements into detailed specifications and work plans. Develops and executes work planning related to report development tasks including effort and completion date estimates. Performs to schedule and completes all tasks in the agreed upon timelines. Works independently on assigned tasks with minimal assistance. Develops and maintains supporting documentation (i.e., business requirements documents, design documents, report inventory, etc.). Leads interactions with customers to communicate status, resolve issues, and obtain sign-offs (i.e., design complete, testing complete, and/or ready for promotion). Performs efficient and complete hand-offs to Developers. Reports work status and issues to the Manager of the Analytics Reporting team in a timely manner. Manages competing stakeholder priorities to ensure the highest value is being delivered to customers.Quality Assurance, Communication, and Release Management (20%)Writes, revises, and verifies test procedures to measure report quality. Executes and manages functional and regression tests on reporting solutions. Works with the team to determine and implement agreed upon testing principles and practices. Leads report releases, as required.What you’ll bring to the table: (minimum requirements) Bachelor's degree in Information Systems, Computer Science, or other related field or equivalent combination of education/experience.3+ years experience must include the following:3+ years’ experience performing progressively more complex and responsible Business Analysis and Project Management tasks. 2+ years’ experience working through the complete report development lifecycle. Complete and demonstrable understanding of BI reporting best practices. Knowledge and experience with practices to fully understand business needs and successfully translate business needs into appropriate documentation for systems implementation. Demonstrated excellence in client interaction, analytical skills, written, and verbal communication skills Demonstrated ability to work independently and as part of a team in a cooperative manner. Demonstrated ability to develop creative solutions for academic, instructional, business and research needs. In-depth knowledge of testing methodologies, QA practices, strong diagnostic and problem-solving skills. Demonstrated experience in writing requirements and test specifications. Strong customer focus and management of client expectations; ability to establish and maintain a high level of user trust and confidence in the group. Previous healthcare industry experience. Excellent oral, written and interpersonal communication skills, technical documentation skills, user liason skills, and personal interaction abilities with the ability to convey a positive, professional image in person, on the telephone, and in written correspondence.Ideally, you’ll also have: (desired skills and experience) Knowledge of project management concepts. 3+ years current/recent experience with BI tools, preferably BusinessObjects or Tableau. 3+ years experience working through the complete report development lifecycle. 1+ years experience with Epic reporting including an Epic Data Model certification. Knowledge of health concepts. Strong understanding of data warehousing concepts. Experience with formal project management methods desirable. Demonstrated analytical ability to effectively perform all phases of projects.What are some of the other tidbits that you might want to know?Information Technology deadline-driven environment. Interacts with a variety of individuals within UW Medicine and ITS specifically. Must lead projects without direct supervisory authority. Program operates within the confines of standard IT methodology: Design Review, IT Project Management, Change Control, Risk Assessment, and Code Management. Must work within the constraints of multiple technical environments. The Analytics group services all UW Medicine organizations: Harborview Medical Center, Northwest Hospital & Medical Center, Valley Medical Center, UW Medical Center, UW Neighborhood Clinics, UW Physicians, UW School of Medicine, and Airlift Northwest. Must learn many organizational structures and cultures and foster collaboration. Available to work off-hours and weekends as needed. The majority of work is performed in an office environment during normal business hours Ability to communicate clearly in English, both verbally and in writing. Name: Business Systems Analyst Payments
Description: Posted Date: Nov-21-2018  Job ID: 12567  Job Type: Full Time  Job Function: Information Technology  City: Bellevue  State: Washington  Store: Eastgate Headquarters  What's cool about this job  This Business Systems Analyst Payments position is a critical role with accountability for Business Systems Analysis scoped to business-transformative projects and is involved with projects from inception through implementation. Name: Project Launch Analyst – Finance and Business Integration
Description: Job Description Amazon is a fast paced, dynamic, high-tech Company based in Seattle. Amazon’s finance team is searching for bar-raising accounting professionals who consistently exceed expectations, who thrive in a challenging workplace, and who can actively contribute to our talented team.  This position supports and directly influences the launches of some of Amazon’s newest global business initiatives in the consumer products, digital, merchant services, operations, logistics, payments, and cloud computing lines of business. The senior project launch analyst will work closely with the global financial systems team, accounting operations teams, tax, treasury, and others on new initiatives to provide integrated accounting requirements to the business teams. In addition, the project launch analyst is a member of a project team which partners with our operational accounting and business finance groups in developing strategic solutions to support our high growth rate through launch methodology design and training, creation of accounting tools used to support new launches and design inputs to longer-term platform development. Successful candidates for this position will have a minimum of three years professional experience working with financial processes, project management, accounting requirements documentation, process design, and user acceptance testing responsibilities. They will have developed a passion for delivering process improvement across the accounting organization. This position is expected to have a deep sense of ownership, ability to identify process improvement opportunities, drive positive change across the organization, and enhance partnerships between Accounting and various business and IT groups. In addition successful candidates will be comfortable working in a fast-paced environment, managing through ambiguity and complexity, and demonstrate and ability to support multiple, simultaneous, project launches at any one time. Candidates will be expected to identify and own projects independently, supported by junior analysts where appropriate. Candidates are also expected to have sufficient finance experience to help the project launch team identify and incorporate the necessary financial reporting and internal control elements into the systems or tools that are developed to support new business activities. Excellent communication and organization skills are required along with the ability to anticipate, identify, and communicate risks to accounting, finance, business and IT leadership, and the ability to communicate project information to senior business leadership. Job responsibilities will include: · Working independently to manage projects and support Amazon's business and development teams in the design and implementation of new products and offerings. · Provide project management within and across business units to transition new processes and/or permanent solutions to support the Amazon accounting team. · Coordinate with the global accounting teams to establish and maintain strong communication channels. · Identify, implement, and adhere to best practices across all new project launches · Offering coaching, support, and guidance to direct reports.Basic QualificationsBachelors degree required3 plus years of relevant experience in accountingPreferred QualificationsExcellent interpersonal, written and oral communication skillsDesire to exceed expectations and drive positive change in the organizationExperience of project management and an understanding of project management concepts.Experience working in a fast paced environment similar to a high tech start-upExperience of system and process designProven ability to influence and make an impactExcellent analytical skillsAmazon is an Equal Opportunity-Affirmative Action Employer – Minority / Female / Disability / Veteran / Gender Identity / Sexual Orientation.Apply Now at Amazon

Name: Business Analyst II CPO

Description: Business Analyst IIThe Federal Reserve System Cash Product Office (CPO) has an exciting opportunity for a Business Analyst. In this role in the CPO’s National Operations group, you will support a variety of projects and tasks that may include operations support, inventory management, third party vendor program management, market intelligence, and business resiliency for the Federal Reserve System. The CPO’s primary goal is to provide leadership and strategic direction for the Federal Reserve Cash Services function to ensure continued fulfillment of the Federal Reserve's mission. About the Cash Product Office:The mission of Federal Reserve Cash Services (FedCash® Services) is to supply currency and coin to meet both domestic and international demand, maintain the quality and integrity of currency and coin in circulation, and ensure depository institutions have ready access to Cash Services. The national Cash Product Office (CPO) provides strategic direction and operational support for FedCash® Services. The CPO provides operational guidance and technology strategies for U.S. currency and coin supplied to depository institutions by the twelve Federal Reserve Banks and their branches. In coordination with the Federal Reserve Board of Governors, the CPO formulates policies related to the handling of coin and currency. Highlights of the Position: Prepare, interpret, and present a variety of operational analyses and presentations, including weekly/monthly reports, analyses of large datasets, and recommendations to executive management for decision-making. Name: Sr. Project Launch Analyst Finance and Business Integration
Description: Amazon is a fast paced, dynamic, high-tech Company based in Seattle. Amazons finance team is searching for bar-raising accounting professionals who consistently exceed expectations, who thrive in a challenging workplace, and who can actively contribute to our talented team.  This position supports and directly influences the launches of some of Amazons newest global business initiatives in the consumer products, digital, merchant services, operations, logistics, payments, and cloud computing lines of business. The senior project launch analyst will work closely with the global financial systems team, accounting operations teams, tax, treasury, and others on new initiatives to provide integrated accounting requirements to the business teams. In addition, the project launch analyst is a member of a project team which partners with our operational accounting and business finance groups in developing strategic solutions to support our high growth rate through launch methodology design and training, creation of accounting tools used to support new launches and design inputs to longer-term platform development.  Successful candidates for this senior analyst level position will have a minimum of five years professional experience working with financial processes, project management, accounting requirements documentation, process design, and user acceptance testing responsibilities. They will have developed a passion for delivering process improvement across the accounting organization. This position is expected to have a deep sense of ownership, ability to identify process improvement opportunities, drive positive change across the organization, and enhance partnerships between Accounting and various business and IT groups.  In addition successful candidates will be comfortable working in a fast-paced environment, managing through ambiguity and complexity, and demonstrate and ability to support multiple, simultaneous, project launches at any one time. Candidates will be expected to identify and own projects independently, supported by junior analysts where appropriate. Candidates are also expected to have sufficient finance experience to help the project launch team identify and incorporate the necessary financial reporting and internal control elements into the systems or tools that are developed to support new business activities. Excellent communication and organization skills are required along with the ability to anticipate, identify, and communicate risks to accounting, finance, business and IT leadership, and the ability to communicate project information to senior business leadership. Job responsibilities will include: · Working independently to manage projects and support Amazon's business and development teams in the design and implementation of new products and offerings.  · Provide project management within and across business units to transition new processes and/or permanent solutions to support the Amazon accounting team.  · Coordinate with the global accounting teams to establish and maintain strong communication channels.  · Identify, implement, and adhere to best practices across all new project launches  · Offering coaching, support, and guidance to direct reports.

Name: Business Systems Analyst - Commercial Loans
Description: The Business Systems Analyst will be primarily responsible for providing the leadership, oversight and implementation of the commercial loan platform as well as updates and daily support. In addition, this position will be responsible for the integration if the bank acquires loan portfolios. The Commercial Loan System Administrator will develop appropriate systems and procedures that can be adapted to a range of integrations based on size and complexity to ensure a seamless integration that maximizes client retention. Along with the key functions listed below, this position will be expected to uphold the value that Washington Federal places on simply being nice when serving our co-workers and clients.  ESSENTIAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES include the following. Other duties may be assigned: Maintain the Commercial Loan Platform to meet the business needs.Leads major and minor initiatives to enhance or upgrade the Commercial Loan PlatformProvide production support for issues that arise as well as daily support for tasksPartners with business leadership and other key stakeholders to define opportunities, and to identify and prioritize projects based on predefined criteria (i.e. return on investment, productivity, compliance, etc.).Defines structure and assembles team with subject matter expertise to manage various projects, integration activities and continuity plans.For acquired loans, develop and maintain an integration plan (playbook) that can be adapted to a range of integrations based on size and complexity, and clearly defines roles, responsibilities, tasks, and key milestones.Works closely with Department Heads in early stages to develop pre-close integration plan and strategy.Leads/owns the development and implementation of integration activities.Drives day-to-day execution of the integration process, including coaching cross-functional teams, leading weekly integration team meetings and driving proactive issue resolution.Organizes and communicates current and future integration process standards, best practices and guidelines across transactions.Follow the Bank's Information Security policies, insuring that the processing and handling of all client information and confidential bank information is done in a secure manner and environment. Bachelor's degree in Business Administration, Finance or a related major. Must have demonstrated leadership ability, and create and promote an atmosphere of high integrity, hard work and commitment to the company's values and mission Must also have the ability to accept and facilitate change, caused by client demands, corporate needs, or regulatory requirements, and possess a positive attitude, good judgment, and the ability to accept responsibility and handle confidential information. Name: Business Intel Engineer II
Description: Amazon is seeking an expert Business Intelligence Engineer to play a key role in creating foundational studies, models, and algorithms that influence Amazon's global retail customer experience strategies. This is an opportunity to be on the ground level of a core team; focused on pioneering cutting-edge research. Our small team of scientists and engineers work closely together and are passionate about making bold bets. We get our energy from inventing on behalf of customers and success is measured against the possible, not the probable.  We are looking for a creative thinker with a deep analytics experience who knows how to execute and deliver on big ideas. Ability and enthusiasm to be a leader on a startup team operating in a highly ambiguous environment is required.  As a Business Intelligence Engineer, you will play a key role on the development of advanced analytical projects. You will need to collect information from business teams and build systems, recommendations, and tools that have a global and lasting impact on retail customers. To be successful, you should demonstrate the ability to balance excellent analytical and technical skills while clearly driving communication and collaboration with other key partners. As a member of the team, you will also have the opportunity to leverage your passion for data science to create high impact solutions. Major responsibilities: · Analyze and extract relevant information from large amounts of both structured and unstructured data to help automate and optimize key processes  · Define the business problem and solution approach autonomously with limited guidance.  · Use advanced algorithms to solve business problems, and transform one-off models into automated systems.  · Analyze and validate data to ensure high data quality and reliable insights.  · Partner with data engineering teams to improve data assets, quality, metrics and insights.  · Proactively identify interesting areas for deep dive investigations and future program development.  · Design and execute analytic projects in collaboration with Product Managers, Business Analysts, Economists, and other specialists.  · Challenge assumptions and conventional ways of thinking and work collaboratively with the team to generate new approaches  · Write concise documents communicating results to stakeholders and visualize data to drive decision making

Name: Business Intelligence (BI) Analyst - Digital Marketing
Description: Accelerate Your CareerDrive global technologyWith more than $2 billion in revenues, CDK Global is a leading global provider of integrated information technology and digital marketing solutions to the automotive retail and adjacent industries. Focused on enabling end-to-end automotive commerce, CDK provides solutions to dealers in more than 100 countries around the world, serving approximately 28,000 retail locations and most automotive manufacturers. CDK Global solutions automate and integrate critical processes from pre-sale targeted advertising to the sale, financing, insurance, parts supply, repair and maintenance of vehicles, with an increasing focus on utilizing data analytics and predictive intelligence. We’re large enough to make a difference but small enough for your voice to be heard. This means that we are an organization where every person matters. You can make an impact on the success of our business and that of our customers regardless of what career you decide to pursue.From data scientists to sales and client service experts, we’re hiring to support your growth and ours - Green light your career. CDK Global is hiring a BI Analyst for our Digital Marketing Agency! This position will help guide stakeholders through the process of designing data solutions for clients, while having the technical skills to build and implement those solutions through our Enterprise Data Warehouse. Relocation and/or Visa Sponsorship/Transfer assistance not provided.POSITION OVERVIEW:. This position will think strategically about business issues and will have a strong command of data warehousing platforms, reporting automation, data visualization, digital marketing analytics and basic statistics. . Must be comfortable working directly with stakeholders to understand their concerns, use data to address them, and present the results to a non-technical audience in a clear and concise manner. . A comfortable relationship with various flavors of SQL and experience with a fact/dimension based Data Warehouse is essential.. Knowledge of “Big” data platforms such as Hadoop, and any experience automating data workflows is a plus. . Extracted data will be manipulated, merged, and analyzed to produce reports, graphs, dashboards and other output to ultimately reveal performance of our products for internal and external users. . A history of delivering “actionable insights” to stakeholders is desired. CDK is looking for Analysts who want to go beyond reporting.. The successful candidate will work closely with OEM Consultants, BI Engineers and other Data Analysts. ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS:. Communicate with business consultants, agency partners and enterprise sales to gather and understand requirements. Ability to manage a backlog, establish priorities, multi-task and work proactively and independently. Data mining from data warehouse, using SQL, RegEx, json, pixel logs, and other big data formats. Analyze web analytics and other quantitative and qualitative data. Data discovery and data cleansingKNOWLEDGE, SKILLS AND ABILITIES:. BA/BS in a business or technical field; an Advanced Degree is a plus. 3+ years’ experience in a Data Analyst role. 3+ years with websites & digital media analytics. Must have experience with Google Analytics and SQL. Experience with digital marketing concepts, cookies (1st & 3rd party), pixel tags, privacy standards, SEO, social media, advertising attribution methods & models. Experience with Tableau a plus. Experience with Data Warehousing platforms (Oracle, SQL Server, etc.). Automotive vertical experience a plusCDK Global knows you have passions outside of work. You have family, friends, sporting events, and lots of things going on. That’s why we offer a comprehensive benefits package to not only take care of you but your family as well. All of our benefits are effective the first day of employment including 401K matching, paid time off to re-energize, donate your time to volunteer in your community, and tuition reimbursement to name a few.At CDK, we pride ourselves on having a diverse workforce. We value and celebrate the uniqueness of individuals and the different perspectives they provide. We offer equal opportunity employment regardless of race, color, religion, gender, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, genetics, disability status, age, marital status, or protected veteran status.

Name: Project Launch Analyst Finance and Business Integration
Description: Amazon is a fast paced, dynamic, high-tech Company based in Seattle. Amazons finance team is searching for bar-raising accounting professionals who consistently exceed expectations, who thrive in a challenging workplace, and who can actively contribute to our talented team.  This position supports and directly influences the launches of some of Amazons newest global business initiatives in the consumer products, digital, merchant services, operations, logistics, payments, and cloud computing lines of business. The senior project launch analyst will work closely with the global financial systems team, accounting operations teams, tax, treasury, and others on new initiatives to provide integrated accounting requirements to the business teams. In addition, the project launch analyst is a member of a project team which partners with our operational accounting and business finance groups in developing strategic solutions to support our high growth rate through launch methodology design and training, creation of accounting tools used to support new launches and design inputs to longer-term platform development.  Successful candidates for this position will have a minimum of three years professional experience working with financial processes, project management, accounting requirements documentation, process design, and user acceptance testing responsibilities. They will have developed a passion for delivering process improvement across the accounting organization. This position is expected to have a deep sense of ownership, ability to identify process improvement opportunities, drive positive change across the organization, and enhance partnerships between Accounting and various business and IT groups.  In addition successful candidates will be comfortable working in a fast-paced environment, managing through ambiguity and complexity, and demonstrate and ability to support multiple, simultaneous, project launches at any one time. Candidates will be expected to identify and own projects independently, supported by junior analysts where appropriate. Candidates are also expected to have sufficient finance experience to help the project launch team identify and incorporate the necessary financial reporting and internal control elements into the systems or tools that are developed to support new business activities. Excellent communication and organization skills are required along with the ability to anticipate, identify, and communicate risks to accounting, finance, business and IT leadership, and the ability to communicate project information to senior business leadership. Job responsibilities will include: · Working independently to manage projects and support Amazon's business and development teams in the design and implementation of new products and offerings.  · Provide project management within and across business units to transition new processes and/or permanent solutions to support the Amazon accounting team.  · Coordinate with the global accounting teams to establish and maintain strong communication channels.  · Identify, implement, and adhere to best practices across all new project launches  · Offering coaching, support, and guidance to direct reports.

Name: Business Process Analyst
Description: Business Process Analyst - City of Bellevue ( Job # 18-00311)  Minimum Salary: $5,568.35 per month Maximum Salary: $7,683.60 per month Employment Type: Full Time  Department: Utilities Open until filled. (Open to current employees and the general public.) Summary The City of Bellevue Utilities Department is responsible for providing water, wastewater, storm drainage, and solid waste services for the City of Bellevue service area. The Department is currently recruiting for a Business Process Analyst. This position provides financial and business process analysis, data analysis, project implementation, budget monitoring, and maintenance support within the Utilities Systems and Finance Groups for Utilities staff and management. Business process responsibilities include interviewing users, documenting user requirements, interpreting and representing data for business intelligence, business case development, user acceptance testing of business systems, and creation of user documentation and training materials. Supported systems include utility billing, asset and work management, voice response and online payment systems, and other systems as needed. Work content includes Utilities SharePoint support and site development and enhancement and support of business process flows. Financial process responsibilities include supporting budget development, financial monitoring and reporting, and special projects as assigned. Financial data analysis and visual representation of data is a critical and regular part of the job.  The City of Bellevue is a dynamic, international and multicultural, future-focused, diversity driven, high performing City. The City invests in its employees and encourages and rewards employee growth and development. Bellevue is noted for its diversity, community involvement, intellectual excitement, artistic pursuits, and natural beauty. The National League of Cities issued Bellevue its Cultural Diversity Award in 2015. Livability.com ranked Bellevue number 14 on its 2015 Top 100 Best Places to Live.  To view the full job description and apply online, please click the apply button above. You will be redirected to a different web site (governmentjobs.com) where you will be able to view the full job announcement and submit your application. Backed by industry-leading companies, the Bluetooth SIG oversees the development of new Bluetooth specifications, and provides the processes and tools for members to build, test, qualify, and brand their Bluetooth products. Name: RECORDS ANALYST
Description: RECORDS ANALYST  Req #: 162567  Department: EXECUTIVE OFFICE OF THE PRESIDENT AND PROVOST  Job Location: Seattle Campus  Posting Date: 11/28/2018  Closing Info: Open Until Filled  Salary: Salary and benefits are competitive. Salary is commensurate with qualifications and experience.  Shift: First Shift  As a UW employee, you have a unique opportunity to change lives on our campuses, in our state and around the world. UW employees offer their boundless energy, creative problem solving skills and dedication to build stronger minds and a healthier world. UW faculty and staff also enjoy outstanding benefits, professional growth opportunities and unique resources in an environment noted for diversity, intellectual excitement, artistic pursuits and natural beauty. All of which has allowed the UW to be nationally recognized as a “Great College to Work For” for five consecutive years. We have an outstanding opportunity for a Records Analyst.Reporting directly to the Senior Director for Finance, HR, and Administration for the Executive Office of the President & Provost, the Records Analyst supports the Executive Office in three main functional areas: Records Management - Directly responsible for developing, implementing, and maintaining of the Executive Office's records management program as well overseeing continual improvements. Conduct analysis of departmental practices and procedures for compliance with internal and external recordkeeping regulations. Design, develop, implement, test, modify, and maintain electronic systems specific to the needs of the department while meeting all applicable policies and regulations. Development of an ongoing maintenance plan and internal training program is a critical component of this position. Documentation of records retention guidelines and expectations as they are developed for business continuity is expected. The Records Analyst assists colleagues with audits, operational tasks, and other special projects as needed. Public Records Requests - Assist office in responding to public requests, including conducting electronic and hard-copy searches, reviewing records for responsiveness and highlighting potential exemptions or other issues, preparing records for transmittal to the UW's Office of Public Records and Open Public Meetings, and consulting with Senior Director as needed regarding public records questions. Inventory - Directly oversee management of office and Presidential residence inventory lists; conduct biennial physical inventory for office and Presidential residence; assist with and oversee other inventory-related matters for office and residence. The Records Analyst supports the diverse needs of the Executive Office through the development and maintenance of a records system which supports a wide range of business operations. Successful candidates must be capable of managing multiple information sources and competing priorities, sometimes with tight deadlines. The Records Analyst must handle records efficiently, reliably, and accurately, while demonstrating professional discretion and independent judgment in all areas of operation. Managing this breadth and complexity requires fostering a good working relationship with colleagues and process partners, an ability to be proactive, a capacity for innovation, and a willingness to embrace change and promote process improvement. This position requires a functional understanding of applicable guidelines, rules, policies, and laws regarding public records, records retention, and inventorying at the University of Washington generally and the Executive Office specifically. Ability to implement policies and procedures to effectively and efficiently meet the requirements identified above and user needs is essential. Duties & ResponsibilitiesRecords Systems ManagementDirectly manage the records management system for the Executive Office of the President & Provost. Exercise independent judgement and decision-making when implementing best practices and departmental procedures for records retention. Conduct analysis of departmental practices and procedures for compliance with internal and external record-keeping regulations and research, develop, recommend, and implement improvements. Design, develop, implement, test, modify, and maintain electronic and physical systems specific to the needs of the department while meeting all applicable policies and regulations. Develop trainings, tutorials, and other guidance materials for colleagues in respect to their obligations for proper records retention. Provide guidance, consultation, and project management support to teams within the Executive Office with regard to developing and implementing internal electronic document management structures and systems. Collaborate with other University departments/programs (e.g. UW-IT, RMS, and EDMS) to further the office's records management goals. Public Records Request ManagementCoordinate Executive Office responses to public records requests, including managing records searches, reviewing record documentation, coordinating with the Office of Public Records and Open Public Meetings, etc. Independently track and prioritize outstanding requests and conduct follow up as needed. Provide guidance and consultation to unit members on proper protocol and procedures in responding to requests. Inventory ManagementOversee Executive Office and Presidential Residence inventorying and responses to audits, subpoenas, and other similar efforts on a scheduled and as-needed basis. Review current inventorial systems/procedures; independently research, develop, and implement process improvements to modernize and streamline processes. Special ProjectsIndependently manage and prioritize special projects as designated by the Senior Director, which may include assisting with audits, reports, or other critical tasks. Conduct research, gather materials and resources, and report on status and progress. Requirements include:Bachelor's Degree in Information Technology, Business, Communications, English, or related field Two years accumulated work experience, including experience in records management, including experience in developing, implementing, and maintaining records systems; complying with and implementing records retention schedule and experience in introducing and implementing new systems and processes. Project management experience Strong analytical and problem-solving skills Excellent communication skills, both written and verbal High level of attention to detail and accuracy Demonstrated high level of professionalism and judgement Ability to work independently with a high degree of reliability, accuracy and productivity Ability to work, coordinate, and communicate with diverse audiences Substantial experience and skill using common software programs such as Microsoft Word, Excel, and PowerPoint Equivalent education/experience will substitute for all minimum qualifications except when there are legal requirements, such as a license/certification/registration. Additionally, you will play a key role in supporting the vision for business analytics, solutions architecture for data related business constructs, as well as tactical execution such as campaign performance reporting. Ultimately, you are paving the way for high quality, high-velocity decisions making in support of growth.  For this role, we're looking for an experienced data analyst who will be responsible for data instrumentation, dashboard/report building, metrics reviews, inform channel investments, guidance on success/failure metrics and ad hoc analysis. You will also have the opportunity to interact with technical and non-technical staff members throughout the company, and your effort will have a direct impact on hundreds of stakeholders at Twitch. Responsibilities · Evangelize data knowledge and insights: manage communications with your stakeholders and other teams, collaborate with both technical and non-technical colleagues to complete data projects and ensure all parties can use the insights to further improve.  · Maintain a customer-centric focus: strive to be a domain and product expert through data, develop trust amongst your peers and stakeholders, and ensure that your team has access to data to make decisions.  · Prioritize and execute in the face of ambiguity: work with stakeholders and mentors to distill the problem, adapt your tools to answer complicated questions, and identify the trade-offs between speed and quality of different approaches.  · Create analytical frameworks to measure team success: partner with cross-functional teams to define success metrics, create approaches to track the data and troubleshoot errors, quantify and evaluate the data, then develop a common language for all colleagues to understand these KPIs.  · Support data processes - provide the team with ad-hoc analysis, automated dashboards, and self-service reporting tools so that everyone gets a good sense of the state of the business

Description: FINANCIAL ANALYST  Req #: 162512  Department: UNIVERSITY ADVANCEMENT  Job Location: Seattle Campus  Posting Date: 11/28/2018  Closing Info: Open Until Filled  Salary: Salary and benefits are competitive. Salary is commensurate with qualifications and experience.  Shift: First Shift  Notes: As a UW employee, you will enjoy generous benefits and work/life programs. For a complete description of our benefits for this position, please visit our website, click here. First consideration will be given to those who apply by December 19, 2018 As a UW employee, you have a unique opportunity to change lives on our campuses, in our state and around the world. UW faculty and staff also enjoy outstanding benefits, professional growth opportunities and unique resources in an environment noted for diversity, intellectual excitement, artistic pursuits and natural beauty. All of which has allowed the UW to be nationally recognized as a “Great College to Work For” for five consecutive years. The Advancement Finance team plans and administers unit-wide financial and budgetary policy development, financial information systems planning and integration, and departmental business, budgeting and finance administration. The Advancement Finance team supports all central Advancement operations and 25 campus constituencies, the 501(c)(3) for the UW Alumni Association, and the UW Foundation in achieving their budgeting and finance goals by providing expertise and assistance in the areas of business and systems administration. The Advancement Finance team consults, advises and makes recommendations to Advancement Leadership in planning, developing and launching a strategic projects, programs and service initiatives. University Advancement has an outstanding opportunity for a Financial Analyst. The Financial Analyst is responsible for financial reporting, analysis and auditing of University Advancement, as well as the 501(c) (3) organizations for both UW Alumni Association and UW Foundation. Financial analysis includes, but is not limited to: cash flow management, development, implementation and review of budgets; development, maintenance and review of financial information systems; forecasting; analyses of financial data, monitoring financial performance, making recommendations and producing financial statements and management reports, and assisting the Director of Finance & Administration with ad hoc duties including monitoring investment returns, internal controls and risk management assessments. Duties and ResponsibilitiesMaintain and review existing accrual-based accounting system and financial information and reporting system for University Advancement to facilitate accurate and timely financial and management reporting. Forecast and report budget status. Using trending analysis, make budget and finance recommendations to Advancement leadership on future courses of action. Work together with the Director of F&A to perform financial functions, correct fiscal entries, advise of potential budget deficits/overruns, control expenditures and safeguard the department’s assets. Provide recommendations on long-range strategic fiscal planning, budget projections and fiscal strategy plans for Advancement, UW Alumni Association and UW Foundation and assists all departments in long-range budget forecasting. Develop and implement budget plan for state budgets, self-sustaining budgets, gifts and discretionary accounts. Provide analyses and spending recommendations through an understanding of Advancement policies and practices and adherence to organizational values. Works with the Finance team to reach mutually acceptable deliverables using available resources and opportunities. Provide consultation on the production of the monthly budget and expenditure reports for individual departments. Advise and consult with the finance team to ensure adherence to budget and compliance with policies. Oversee and manage budget encumbrance and expenditure reports on a regular basis. Manages monthly statement of activities and balance sheets and reconciles financial statements for all funds. Together with the Director, manage cash flow to ensure availability of funds to support the UW Alumni Association’s and UW Foundation’s activities. Oversee the management of the 501(c) (3) financial operation for UW Alumni Association and the UW Foundation, including creation and maintenance of monthly accounting report and balance sheet. Maintain timely compliance with all federal and state tax filings and status renewals. Keep abreast of FASB accounting standards and emerging issues. Manage and oversee annual audit activities with independent external auditors. Establish, cultivate and negotiate contracts and service agreements with outside vendors and suppliers to maintain a viable business structure. Maintain relationships with outside bankers, insurance brokers, auditors, tax accountants. Ensures proper filing and payment of all applicable federal and local taxes, including unrelated business income taxes. Participates in other duties as assigned by the Director of Finance & Administration. RequirementsBachelor's degree in Business Administration, Finance or Accounting and 5 years of progressively responsible relevant experience in accounting and financial planning and budgeting in mid to large size complex organization. Equivalent combination of education and experience may be considered. Proficiency using PC computers. Demonstrated strong computer skills, including proficiency with Microsoft Word, Excel, and PowerPoint for correspondence, special reports, spreadsheets, databases, forms, etc. Key CompetenciesCoreEffective communications: Expresses oneself clearly and empathetically in interactions with others in all forms of communication, i.e., verbal and written, one-on-one and group, etc. Interpersonal Awareness:  Builds and maintains positive relationships and actively contributes as a member of working teams to achieve results. Professional Credibility: Takes responsibility for meeting goals, objectives, obligations, and solving problems while representing the mission, vision and values of the organization. Critical Thinking: Obtains, analyzes and evaluates information effectively in the face of ambiguity. Makes appropriate decisions based on relevant information and experience. Ethics and Trust: Models and upholds the values of candor, openness, inclusiveness and honesty despite internal and external pressures. Acts consistently with Washington State ethical guidelines and organizational core values and beliefs. Valuing Diversity & Inclusiveness: Respects, values and contributes to the UW’s commitment to inclusiveness and diversity. Functional ExpertiseStrategic Agility : Anticipates emerging trends; can articulate a clear sense of goals that align with organization’s mission, vision, and values. Organizational Acumen: Ability to size up a situation, balance reason and the interest of others, and act in a decisive, timely and appropriate manner that is congruent with the organization's values, goals and mission to achieve success. Planning & Implementing: Ability to develop strategies, measures for success and feasible timelines for volunteer stewardship. Managing Conflict: Recognizes and addresses conflicts and disagreements in a safe and respectful environment, manages conflicts collaboratively, and builds consensus with the best interests of the organization in mind. Desired QualificationsCPA certification. Non-Profit, development or advancement operations and/or accounting experience. Knowledge of UW systems including Workday, FIN, BGT, ARIBA, and FinDesktop. Knowledge of Abila MIP Fund Accounting, nonprofit accounting software. Name: HRIS Analyst
Description: As a UW employee, you will enjoy generous benefits and work/life programs. For detailed information on Benefits for this position, click here. As a UW employee, you have a unique opportunity to change lives on our campuses, in our state and around the world. UW employees offer their boundless energy, creative problem solving skills and dedication to build stronger minds and a healthier world.  UW faculty and staff also enjoy outstanding benefits, professional growth opportunities and unique resources in an environment noted for diversity, intellectual excitement, artistic pursuits and natural beauty. All of which has allowed the UW to be nationally recognized as a "Great College to Work For" for four consecutive years.  The Human Resources department's mission is to support UW faculty and staff in successfully meeting the goals of the University by providing high quality and responsive human resources support to foster an exceptional work environment that encourages, nurtures and recognizes the professional development of University employees. The department's vision is to create a premier HR organization whose staff members are dedicated to the goal of working together to provide the highest possible quality of services in carrying out its mission.  HR Information Systems has an outstanding full time opportunity for a HRIS Analyst.  The purpose of this position is to provide technical support to UW HRIS systems and processes in preparation for upcoming UW Enterprise projects. This role will partner with current business analysts and developers to analyze, interpret and document business and technical requirements for various HRIS systems, provide support for information and data requests, and produce technical outputs described below. This role reports to the Director of HRIS and is currently funded for 1 year. Understanding UW's Operating Environment: This position must develop a working understanding of Human Resources' business activities and related information systems needs/projects. HRIS information management services cross systems that include payroll, recruiting, layoff, time and leave, reporting (labor, internal, public, state and federal). Each of these systems includes a variety of differing rules, data governance policies and procedures. Dimensions and Impact: This position has a direct impact on HRIS information services delivery capability. Errors in the extraction, analysis and production of data can have significant impacts on university decisions, the accuracy and completeness of public records requests and other electronic records management functions. RESPONSIBILITIES: Information Management & Support  Information Management efforts such as report development, information and records requests and learning HR's data are a key portion of HRIS work and this role. This position requires strong SQL skills that will be used to pull, aggregate, and document large data sets. This position will also be developing Microsoft Reporting Services Reports, and using tools such as Office Writer and Enesys reporting tool to present data in an application layer to HRIS customers.  Business and Support Analysis  This role will also serve as a member of the HRIS support team, some effort will be focused on making HRIS work better for our customers on an ongoing basis. Assisting with analysis and documentation of as is state, future state, gap analysis, requirements, user documentation and test plans for HR projects, This could include pulling data and synthesizing information for the business analyst, assisting in describing and documenting information used in current HRIS systems, working with support analyst to  troubleshoot and assist customers using HRIS systems and working with the internal HRIS support team to provide better tools and services for our customers.  Miscellaneous  Other duties as assigned. REQUIREMENTS: Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Information Management, or Business or related field and four to five years of experience. Experience can replace education. Specific Skills: Minimum of 2 years using SQL (or programming languages) to extract and present data out of complex multi-layer environments.  Minimum of 2 years working with business clients to develop requirements and system documentation.  Minimum of 2 years developing enterprise level reports in a production environment.  Minimum of 2 years' experience analyzing and explaining complex data sets.  Minimum of 3 years' experience working within the IT industry.  Equivalent education/experience will substitute for all minimum qualifications except when there are legal requirements, such as a license/certification/registration. DESIRED: Ideal applicant will have excellent verbal and written communication skills.  Ideal applicant will work well as part of a team, but is also able to work independently when needed.  Ideal applicant will have experience with the Microsoft BI suite including reporting services, SSIS, and SSAS. CONDITIONS OF EMPLOYMENT: This position is funded for approximately one year, contingent upon continued funding. Name: CREDIT ANALYST US PBI
Description: Amazon is looking for a smart, motivated, and analytical Credit Analyst to join our US Amazon Lending team. He or she will have responsibility for providing Amazon Business customers with a leading experience and a thorough credit risk assessment as they apply for Amazons Pay-by-Invoice (PBI) feature. This will involve high judgment and frequent interaction with customers and internal stakeholders to ensure decisions are sound and well understood. The Credit Analyst will also support the monitoring and management of the entire PBI accounts receivable portfolio. The successful candidate will have a strong desire in innovating processes, strong attention to detail and exceed expectations in a dynamic, fast-paced and often ambiguous environment. The position requires an individual who can work autonomously in a fast paced, highly demanding and often ambiguous environment.  This role will report into the US PBI Business Manager and is based in Seattle, WA.  Amazon Business represents an incredible opportunity to address a vast new market segment and customer base and is an area of high interest for Amazon. We are focused on building solutions that enable our business customers to find, research, and buy products and services from a vast selection, across multiple devices, marketplaces and regions. These business customers include individual professionals, small businesses to large institutions (and everything in between). The needs of these business customers are different from those of the traditional Amazon customer, so we are reinventing everything from how we display our selection, price our products, and provide the right customer experience. Initial offerings of PBI include the US, Germany, UK and Japan. We believe we are in a unique position to serve Amazon Business customers with exceptional value due to our deep understanding and insight into our base coupled with our data-grounded analytic and customer-focused approach to building products. Key areas of responsibility include: Evaluate credit applications analyzing data from financial statements, credit reference agencies, application forms and other third party sources to arrive at fast, fair, and appropriate credit decisions  Communicate with customers requires strong Customer Obsession as an Amazon representative in credit-related communication with Amazon Business customers  Improve processes work with internal teams to understand the systems and variables that affect credit management decisions, and drive improvements in the logic, tools and processes, with emphasis on automating tasks that are currently performed manually  Monitor credit performance monitoring of Accounts Receivables with emphasis on financial transactions such as invoices, credits, debit-notes and cash application  Professional traits not unique to this position, but necessary for Amazon leaders in this role include:  Exhibits excellent judgment  Is passionate about customers  Is creative, and data driven  Has relentlessly high standards  Thinks strategically, but stays on top of tactical execution  Results oriented

Name: AWS WW Solutions Architecture Business Analyst
Description: Are you interested in building the data foundation for helping scale the growth of the Solutions Architecture function with Amazon Web Services? In a fast-paced, high-growth environment, making data driven decisions is critical. The Amazon Web Services Solutions Architecture (SA) organization is looking for a Business Analyst to better enable our decision making through the use of data analytics.  The role is critical and highly visible across the organization and plays a key role in developing analytic insights. The insights are used to lead decision making around resource allocation, program effectiveness, productivity analysis and business impact. Consumers of these insights will include individual SAs, SA and Sales management, and AWS senior and executive leadership.  The successful candidate is analytical and possesses a strong passion for developing insights. In addition, you must be able to articulate how the data should be used in decision making. This requires excellent business acumen and communication skills as well as the ability to work with business leaders to develop and define key business questions. Lastly, the successful candidate will also be able to work with BI and software development teams to set up the right data structure and collect information and design the analysis model that answers these questions. You should be passionate about working with data, be driven to dive deep, and be passionate in socializing business impacts to guide the broader organization.

Name: Senior Financial Analyst
Description: Amazon seeks a Senior Financial Analyst to join the Financial Planning & Analysis group to support the DAC (Digital, Advertising and Corp Dev) Financial Planning and Analysis Team. Our team interacts daily with global finance leaders within WW Advertising, WW Digital Video, WW Digital Music and CloudDrive. This role will design new and enhance existing reports and models that make our data more actionable and will own reporting functions during the various planning and reporting phases in finance.  The successful candidate will have the ability to tackle multiple projects and efficiently execute deliverables. The right individual will have strong communication skills and solid business acumen capable of driving results and improving processes. The successful candidate must be able to think and act both strategically and tactically. Strong oral and written communication skills are crucial, as well as ability to think clearly, analyze quantitatively, problem-solve and prioritize. Key Responsibilities include: · Interact with Finance stakeholders at multiple levels to understand business drivers of monthly variance  · Develop and report accurate, actionable, and timely financial and business metrics for monthly, quarterly and annual reviews  · Monitor and enhance existing processes and controls  · Manage the financial planning / budgeting process  · Lead and influence different stakeholders  · Develop ad hoc business analysis and present recommendations to department leaders  · Ability to work on multiple projects with aggressive deadlines

Name: Business Analyst, Prime Video, Costing & Audit
Description: Prime Video seeks an Business Analyst to lead the Digital Video Store analytic efforts surrounding royalty payments and external studio audits. Prime Video is growing at a rapid pace resulting in a dynamic work environment with many opportunities to dive deep into the systems, processes, and data within the royalties costing and payment space.  The primary mission of this role is to drive operational excellence in our pricing, costing, and royalty payment processes by developing health metrics and KPIs. This individual will engage with external studio audit teams directly providing data, information, and analyses to support audit initiatives. A successful candidate will be a self-starter, a quick learner, and an understanding of how financial and accounting operations flow to the business partners financial statements.  This role may differ from a typical Business Analyst role with a strong focus on pricing, costing, and analyzing royalty payments. Success in this role requires strong interpersonal and communication skills. Overall Job Responsibilities: · Work with internal business partners and technology teams to understand, measure and improve profitability and first-time accuracy in royalty payments.  · Perform high level analysis and work with complex data, utilizing operational excellence skills to ensure the audit results are accurate and timely.  · Conduct audit meetings with various teams focused on the key operational items and areas of opportunity to correct historical gaps in vendor management to improve financial performance. External Partner Audits: · Demonstrate advanced analytical skills and the ability to dive deep into the details, while also acknowledging, understanding and applying the detailed analytics to the big picture.  · Analyze monthly reporting for accuracy and compliance with terms.  · Improve documentation, track progress and performance, coordinate all improvement efforts, monitor process improvement effectiveness, and regularly communicate and present to leadership teams.

Name: PROGRAM OPERATIONS ANALYST
Description: PROGRAM OPERATIONS ANALYST Req #: 161094 Department: UW FACILITIES: FINANCE & BUSINESS SERVICES Appointing Department Web Address: https://facilities.uw.edu/ Job Location: Seattle Campus Posting Date: 10/04/2018 Closing Info: Open Until Filled Salary:Salary and benefits are competitive. Salary is commensurate with qualifications and experience. Shift: First Shift As a UW employee, you have a unique opportunity to change lives on our campuses, in our state and around the world. UW employees offer their boundless energy, creative problem solving skills and dedication to build stronger minds and a healthier world.  UW faculty and staff also enjoy outstanding benefits, professional growth opportunities and unique resources in an environment noted for diversity, intellectual excitement, artistic pursuits and natural beauty. All of which has allowed the UW to be nationally recognized as a “Great College to Work For” for five consecutive years.  Facilities Services (FS) is a world-class organization providing exceptional services anywhere, anytime in support of the University of Washington’s mission of teaching, research, and discovery. FS engages employees through LEAN practices and continuous improvement. FS includes eight departments that operate, maintain and support the University: Building Services Department, Campus Engineering & Operations, Emergency Management, Facilities Employee Services, Facilities Maintenance & Construction, Finance and Business Services, Integrated Operations & Engagement and Transportation Services. Our staff must exhibit an appreciation of, a sensitivity to, and respect for a diverse academic environment, inclusive of students, faculty and staff of many social, economic, cultural, ideological, racial and ethnic backgrounds.  Finance & Business Services has an outstanding opportunity for a Program Operations Analyst to be responsible for user analysis of recently implemented functionality of new transportation/parking software and hardware systems. This includes user customer needs analysis, identifying best process for data retrieval and analysis and developing reporting to assist in product, facility and financial analysis. The position will be responsible for documenting processes. The person filling this position will be required to independently plan and manage their work, set priorities and provide deliverables to meet deadlines based on user unit requests, balancing project work with the day-to-day needs of the department. It also requires strong interpersonal skills to understand unit customer needs and communicate system information in a manner that is understandable to non-technical audiences.  This position is a member of the Facilities Finance and Business Services (FABS) IT team. Duties and Responsibilities Reporting to and working under the direction of the FABS IT Manager of Program Operations and collaborating with the Transportation Services team, the person in this position will perform the following duties:  The Analyst will be responsible for the development of analysis and reporting for the ongoing use of the parking systems functionality including the Wheels, T2, License Plate Recognition (LPR), and other parking applications: PARCs (Parking Access and Revenue Control)Gatehouse Permit SalesArranged Parking The Analyst will research and analyze end user requests, review Transportation Services business rules and process documents, and evaluate change requests as well as collaborate with TS stakeholders and vendors to develop policy and procedure design within the parking systems configuration to meet department requirements. Configuration includes but is not limited to system set up for facilities and related use rules and policy, products. The person in this position will interpret technical documentation/requests from parking systems vendors as it relates to configuration and reporting. The Analyst, in collaboration with TS stakeholders, will refine reporting needs and prioritize within existing resources.  On an ongoing basis, analyze and evaluate initial policy, procedure and parking systems configuration decisions and results and provide recommendations for improvements responding to the direction of parking products and maturation of the system. As upgrades and new features are released, evaluate impact to TS use and assist in the development of policy and procedures accordingly.  Update configuration document according to process and approval through the Configuration Management meetings. Analyze, test and configure options for various work group evaluations. Document work group results in system configuration. Support operational units with documentation and training in the event of system changes.  Update training documents as necessary as processes are updated and work with unit stakeholders to quality control documents for training purposes. Provide training to staff as necessary to ensure processes are maintained. Develop queries and associated instruments for auditing performance of processes with process training. Evaluate gaps in performance and work with stakeholders to develop recommendations to improve, configurations, processes and performance.  Provide analysis of system issues, reviewing parking systems reporting and recommending corrections, remotely and in the field.
